4/23/19, 9:14 PM - +91 99788 14667: ***** *Cycling v/s Economy* ***

Sanjay Thakrar, CEO at Euro Axim Bank Ltd.  got economists thinking when he said :

*A cyclist is a disaster for the country's economy*

1- He does not buy the car & does not take car loan

2- Does not buy car insurance

3- Does not buy Fuel

4- Does not send his car for servicing & repairs

5- Does not use paid Parking

6- Does not become Obese

7- Yes,.....and well, damn it !!  *Healthy people are not needed for economy.* They do not buy drugs. They do not go to Hospitals & Doctors.

8-A car runs on your money & saves your fat
*A cycle runs on your fat & saves your money*

9-They add nothing to country's *GDP.*

10-On the contrary, every new McDonald outlet creates at least 30 jobs - 10 Cardiologists, 10 Dentists, 10 weight loss experts apart from people working in McDonald outlet.

*So,  Mr. Economist who do you want?*

*A Cyclist* or 
*A McDonald ?*

6/20/19, 10:11 PM - +91 99788 14667: *Rujuta Diwekar* is the highest paid *dietician* in India. She is the one who took care of *junior Ambani* to lose 108 kgs. 
*Her advice to diabetics*:

1. *Eat fruits grown locally* ..... Banana, Grapes, Chikoo, Mangoes. All fruits have FRUCTOSE so it doesn't matter that you are eating a mango over an Apple. A Mango comes from Konkan and Apple from Kashmir. So Mango is more local to you. 

*Eat all the above fruits in DIABETES as the FRUCTOSE* will eventually manage your SUGAR

  2. Choose Seed oils than Veggie oils. Like choose ground nut, mustard, coconut & til. *Don't choose chakachak packing oils*, like olive,  rice bran etc 
*Go for kachchi ghani oils than refined oils* 

  3. Rujuta spends max time in her talks talking about GHEE and its benefits.
*Eat GHEE daily*. How much GHEE we should eat depends on food. Few foods need more GHEE then eat more and vice versa. Eat ample *GHEE. It REDUCES cholesterol*.

  4. *Include COCONUT.* Either scraped coconut over food like poha, khandvi or chutney with idli and dosa 
Coconut has *ZERO CHOLESTEROL* and it makes your WAIST SLIM 

  5. *Don't eat oats, cereals for breakfast*. They are packaged food and we don't need them.  Also they are tasteless and boring and our day shouldn't start with boring stuff. 
Breakfast should be poha, upma, idli, dosa, paratha 

  6. Farhaan Akhtar's New ad of biscuits - fibre in every bite... Even ghar ka kachara has fibre, likewise oats have fibre. Don't chose them for fibre. *Instead of oats, eat poha, upma, idli, dosa* 

  7. *No JUICES till you have teeth* in your mouth to chew veggies and fruits

  8. *SUGARCANE is the real DETOX* . Drink the juice fresh or eat the SUGARCANE 

  9. For pcos, thyroid - do strength training and weight training and avoid all packaged food 

10. *RICE - eat regular WHITE RICE. NO NEED of Brown rice.* Brown rice needs 5-6 whistles to cook and when it tires your pressure cooker, then why do you want to tire your tummy. 

A white rice is hand pounded simple rice 

*Rice* is not high is GI INDEX.  Rice has mediun GI index and by eating it with daal / dahi / kadhi we bring its GI index further down 
If we take _ghee over this daal chawal then the GI INDEX is brought further down._
*B.* Rice has some rich minerals and you can eat it even three times a day 

11. How much should we eat - *eat more if you are more hungry,* let your stomach be your guide and vice versa 

12. We can *eat rice and chapati together* or only rice if you wish. It depends on your hunger. *Eat RICE in ALL THREE MEALS without any fear.*

13. Food shouldn't make you scared like eating rice and ghee. *Food should make you FEEL GOOD* 

14. *NEVER* look at *CALORIES*. Look at *NUTRIENTS*

15. *No bread, biscuits, cakes, pizza, pasta* 

16. Ask yourself is this the food my Nani & Dadi ate?  If yes then eat without fear. 

17. Eat as per your season. *Eat pakoda, fafda, jalebi in monsoon*. Your hunger is as per season. Few seasons we need fried food so eat them. 

18. When not to have chai - tea - don't drink tea as the first thing in morning or when you are hungry. Rest you can have it 2-3 times a day and with sugar 

19. *NO GREEN tea please.* No green, yellow, purple, blue tea. 

20. Eat *ALL* of your *TRADITIONAL* foods. 

21. Strictly *NO* to packaged foods / drinks.

22. *Exercise / Walk* 
 to digest & stay healthy.

тАУ рккрк▓рк╛рк│рлЗрк▓рлА ркоркЧрклрк│рлА ркмрлНрк▓ркб рк╕рк░ркХрлНркпрлБрк▓рлЗрк╢рки ркХркирлНркЯрлНрк░рлЛрк▓ ркХрк░рлАркирлЗ рк╢рк░рлАрк░ркирлЗ рк╣рк╛рк░рлНркЯ ркПркЯрлЗркХ ркдрлЗркоркЬ ркЕркирлНркп рк╣рк╛рк░рлНркЯ рккрлНрк░рлЛркмрлНрк▓ркоркерлА ркмркЪрк╛рк╡рлЗ ркЫрлЗ. ркдрлЗркерлА рк╣рк╛рк░рлНркЯркирлБркВ рк╕рлНрк╡рк╛рк╕рлНркеркп рк╕рк╛рк░рлБркВ рк░рк╛ркЦрк╡рк╛ ркорк╛ркЯрлЗ ркоркЧрклрк│рлА ркЦрк╛рк╡рлБркВ рк▓рк╛ркнркХрк╛рк░рлА ркЫрлЗ.

тАУ ркмрк╛рк│ркХрлЛркирлЗ рк╕рк╡рк╛рк░рлЗ рккрк▓рк╛рк│рлЗрк▓рлА ркоркЧрклрк│рлАркирк╛ ркерлЛркбрк╛ ркжрк╛ркгрк╛ ркЦрк╡ркбрк╛рк╡рк╡рк╛ркерлА ркдрлЗркорк╛ркВ рк░рк╣рлЗрк▓рк╛ рк╡рк┐ркЯрк╛ркорк┐рки ркЖркВркЦрлЛркирлА рк░рлЛрк╢ркирлА ркЕркирлЗ ркорлЗркорк░рлА рк╢рк╛рк░рлНркк ркХрк░рлЗ ркЫрлЗ. ркоркЧрклрк│рлА ркЦрк╛рк╡рк╛ркерлА рк╢рк░рлАрк░рк░ркорк╛ркВ рк░ркХрлНркдркирлА ркКркгркк ркжрлВрк░ ркерк╛ркп ркЫрлЗ. ркдрлЗркирк╛ркерлА рк╢рк░рлАрк░ркорк╛ркВ ркЙрк░рлНркЬрк╛ ркЕркирлЗ рк╕рлНрклрлВрк░рлНркдрк┐ рккркг ркмркирлА рк░рк╣рлЗ ркЫрлЗ.

10/25/19, 5:55 AM - Ankurbhai Sheth: Have Very beautiful Diwali time 

While we all light our houses , do spend some time today to light a few lamps inside you and sit in silence with your eyes closed... 

Light the first lamp inside you and let it burn your anger and / or jealousy that you may have for any one till date; see it melt away...

Light the second lamp and let it burn away unwanted greed and desires... feel happy and contented with what you have been blessed with.

Light the third lamp and let it fade away all insecurities that you may have in your mind related to anything or financials; just beleive that God has given u life and he will surely give you enough to survive.

Light the 4th lamp and carry that lamp to each part of ur body; let it burn away all your diseased cells or any disease in making. Feel healthy as this lamp travels to each body part and illuminates each organ. 

The 5th lamp is a miniature of the Sun... nothing but the divine light... light it in the centre of your body and let it fill the warmth and love inside your whole body...feel one with the Divine... let the love and warmth filled inside you ooze out of you through your smile...eyes..speech..and body....carry this love with you through out the day...you will find that everyone who meets you is happy and elated. This is the biggest blessing that whoever meets you becomes happier after meeting you... this will also make you happier in return.

Light these 5 lamps each day morning and carry the positivity wherever you go...

Wish you all a very happy Diwali in advance

11/12/19, 7:51 AM - Mom: тАЬKODRIтАЭ , RICE LIKE GRAIN, HELPS FIGHT DIABETES AND OTHERS. 


тАЬKodriтАЭ, is a wild husked millet. It yields a white rice like grain when de husked, which fights diabetes, obesity, besides being antirheumatic. It heals wounds and also acts as a tranquiliser! These findings are not that of any quack, but that of an eminent, learned scientist who has been researching into medicinal properties of herbs for a life time at BarodaтАЩs M.S. University as Head of Botony Dept., and is now heading his own research institution at Baroda. 
Prof. M. Daniel, is a scientist renowned for his research relating to medicinal properties of plants and herbs. He revealed this information in a talk with тАЬTimes of IndiaтАЭ recently.
тАЬKodriтАЭ is cultivated in several states of India and in many other countries, for its grain and use as fodder. After de husking, the white rice like grain is to be cooked and used like rice. тАЬSince ancient times, тАЬKodriтАЭ is consumed as a food by diabetic patients since traditionally it was believed that it reduces sugar level.тАЭ He mentioned that тАЬrecent experiments proved that aqueous and ethanolic extracts administered in required dosages, helped bring down Fasting Blood Sugar (FBG) levels. 
The extracts of тАЬKodriтАЭ, responsible for anti diabetic property possesses anti diabetic compounds such as quercetin and phenollic acids like vanillic acid syringic acid, sys ferrulic acid, phydroxybenzoic acid and melilotic acid. . 
тАЬThe data on the phyto chemicals of тАЬKhodriтАЭ substantiates the anti diabetic property exhibited by this grainтАЭ, said Prof. M. Daniel in the TOI interview. тАЬKhodriтАЭ can be grown even in poor soil conditions or even in stony soils.

рдЖрдкрдиреЗ рдкреБрд╖реНрдЯрд┐рдорд╛рд░реНрдЧ рдХреЗ рдкреНрд░рддреАрдХ (рд░рд╛рдЧ, рднреЛрдЧ рдПрд╡рдВ рд╢реНрд░реГрдВрдЧрд╛рд░) рдХрд╛ рд╡рд╛рд╕реНрддрд╡рд┐рдХ рд╡рд┐рдХрд╛рд╕ рдХрд┐рдпрд╛. рд╡рд┐рдХреНрд░рдо рд╕рдВрд╡рдд 1588 рдореЗрдВ 16 рд╡рд░реНрд╖ рдХреА рдЖрдпреБ рдореЗрдВ рдЖрдкрдХрд╛ рд╡рд┐рд╡рд╛рд╣ рд╢реНрд░реА рд░реБрдХреНрдордгреА рдмрд╣реВрдЬреА рдХреЗ рд╕рд╛рде рд╣реБрдЖ рдЬрд┐рдирд╕реЗ рдЖрдкрдХреЛ рдЫрдГ рдкреБрддреНрд░ рдПрд╡рдВ рдЪрд╛рд░ рдкреБрддреНрд░рд┐рдпрд╛рдБ рд╣реБрдИ. рд╢реНрд░реА рд░реБрдХреНрдордгреА рдмрд╣реВрдЬреА рдХреЗ рд▓реАрд▓рд╛рдкреНрд░рд╡реЗрд╢ рдХреЗ рдкрд╢реНрдЪрд╛рдд рдЧреЭрд╛ рдХреА рд░рд╛рдиреА рджреБрд░реНрдЧрд╛рд╡рддреА рдЬреА рдХреЗ рдЕрддрд┐ рдЖрдЧреНрд░рд╣ рдХреЗ рдХрд╛рд░рдг рд╢реНрд░реА рдкрджреНрдорд╛рд╡рддреА рдЬреА рдХреЗ рд╕рд╛рде рдЖрдкрдХрд╛ рджреНрд╡рд┐рддреАрдп рд╡рд┐рд╡рд╛рд╣ рд╣реБрдЖ рдЬрд┐рдирд╕реЗ рдЖрдкрдХреЛ рдПрдХ рдкреБрддреНрд░ рд╣реБрдП. 
рдЗрд╕ рдкреНрд░рдХрд╛рд░ рдЖрдкрдХреЛ рдХреБрд▓ рд╕рд╛рдд рдкреБрддреНрд░ рдПрд╡рдВ рдЪрд╛рд░ рдкреБрддреНрд░рд┐рдпрд╛рдБ рд╣реБрдИ. рдЖрдкрдХрд╛ рдЧреГрд╣рд╕реНрдерд╛рд╢реНрд░рдо рдЕрддреНрдпрдВрдд рд╕реБрдЦрдкреВрд░реНрд╡рдХ рдмреАрддрд╛. SS
рд╕рднреА рдкреБрддреНрд░ рд╡рд┐рджреНрд╡рд╛рдиреН, рдкреНрд░рддрд┐рднрд╛рд╢рд╛рд▓реА рдПрд╡рдВ рд╕реЗрд╡рд╛рдкрд░рд╛рдпрдг рдереЗ. рдкреБрддреНрд░рд┐рдпрд╛рдБ рднреА рдЪрд┐рддреНрд░рдХрд╛рд░реА, рд╕рдВрдЧреАрдд-рдХрд▓рд╛ рдЖрджрд┐ рдореЗрдВ рдирд┐рдкреБрдг рдПрд╡рдВ рд╕реЗрд╡рд╛рдкрд░рд╛рдпрдг рдереА. рдЖрдкрдиреЗ рд▓реАрд▓рд╛рдкреНрд░рд╡реЗрд╢ рдХреЗ рдкреВрд░реНрд╡ рдЕрдкрдиреЗ рд╕рд╛рддреЛрдВ рдкреБрддреНрд░реЛрдВ рдХреЛ рдмреБрд▓рд╛рдХрд░ рдирд┐рдзрд┐ рдХрд╛ рд╡рд┐рднрд╛рдЬрди рдХрд┐рдпрд╛. 

рдпрд╣рд╛рдБ рдирд┐рдзрд┐ рдХрд╛ рдЕрд░реНрде рдзрди-рджреМрд▓рдд рди рд╣реЛрдХрд░ рднрдЧрд╡рд╛рди рдХреЗ рд╕реЗрд╡реНрдпрд╕реНрд╡рд░реВрдк рдХреА рд╕реЗрд╡рд╛ рдХрд╛ рджрд╛рдпрд┐рддреНрд╡ рд╣реИ. рд╕рд╛рддреЛрдВ рдкреБрддреНрд░реЛрдВ рдХреЛ рдЬреЛ рд╕рд╛рдд рд╕реЗрд╡реНрдпрд╕реНрд╡рд░реВрдк рдкреНрд░рджрд╛рди рдХрд┐рдпреЗ рдЧрдпреЗ, рдЙрд╕рдХреЗ рдЖрдзрд╛рд░ рдкрд░ рдкреБрд╖реНрдЯрд┐рдорд╛рд░реНрдЧ рдореЗрдВ рд╕рд╛рдд рдЧреГрд╣ рдпрд╛ рдкреАрда рдорд╛рдиреЗ рдЬрд╛рддреЗ рд╣реИ рдФрд░ рдкреНрд░рдзрд╛рди рдкреАрда рдирд╛рдерджреНрд╡рд╛рд░рд╛ рдХреА рд╣реИ. 

рд╕рд┐рддреНрддреЗрд░ рд╡рд░реНрд╖ рдХреА рдЖрдпреБ рдореЗрдВ рд╡рд┐рдХреНрд░рдо рд╕рдВрд╡рдд 1642 рдореЗрдВ рдорд╛рдШ рдХреГрд╖реНрдг рд╕рдкреНрддрдореА рдХреЗ рджрд┐рд╡рд╕ рд╢реНрд░реА рдЧрд┐рд░рдзрд░ рдЬреА рдХреЛ рдЕрдЧреНрдирд┐рд╕рдВрд╕реНрдХрд╛рд░ рд╣реЗрддреБ рдЕрдкрдирд╛ рдЙрдкрд░рдирд╛ рджреЗрдХрд░ рдЖрдк рд╕рджреЗрд╣ рд╢реНрд░реА рдЧрд┐рд░рд┐рд░рд╛рдЬ рдЬреА рдХреА рдХрдиреНрджрд░рд╛ рдХреЗ рдорд╛рд░реНрдЧ рд╕реЗ рдирд┐рддреНрдпрд▓реАрд▓рд╛ рдореЗрдВ рдкреНрд░рд╡реЗрд╢ рдХрд░ рдЧрдпреЗ.    

рдЖрдкрдиреЗ рдиреЗ рдкреБрд╖реНрдЯрд┐рдорд╛рд░реНрдЧ рддрдерд╛ рднрд╛рд░рддреАрдп рдзрд░реНрдо рдФрд░ рд╕рдВрд╕реНрдХреГрддрд┐ рдХреА рдЕрдкреВрд░реНрд╡ рд╕реЗрд╡рд╛ рдХреА. рд╡рд╛рд╕реНрддрд╡ рдореЗрдВ рд╢реНрд░реА рдЧреБрд╕рд╛рдВрдИ рдЬреА рдорд╣рд╛рдорд╣рд┐рдорд╛рд╢рд╛рд▓реА рджрд┐рд╡реНрдп рдкреБрд░реВрд╖ рдереЗ, рдЬрд┐рдиреНрд╣реЛрдВрдиреЗ рд╡реИрд╖реНрдгрд╡ рднрдХреНрддрд┐ рдореЗрдВ рдЕрднрд┐рдирд╡ рдЪреЗрддрдирд╛ рдЬрдЧрд╛рдИ.

One day God decided to visit the earth & try some alcohol.

So he changed his dress & went to a bar and asked the bartender :- What all do you have..??

Bartender :- We have Whisky,  Rum, Vodka, Gin, Beer etc etc.

God :- Let's try Whisky first. Give me a bottle of whisky. 

After having full bottle of Whisky, God decided to try Rum.

Bartender was shocked, who is this man..?? After having a bottle of Whisky, he is still on his feet.

After having a bottle of Rum, God decided to have beer.
After having 10 bottles of beer, he asked the bartender for Gin.

Bartender couldn't stop himself asking him :- 

Sir, who are you..?? I've seen people getting drunk after having 4 glasses of whisky and you've almost had 12 bottles and you are still on your feet!!  Who are you..??

God :- рд╣рдо рднрдЧрд╡рд╛рди рд╣реИрдВ

Bartender :- *рдЕрдм рдЪрдврд╝реА*

1. Mom carries for 9 months, Dad carries for 25 years, both are equal, still donтАЩt know why Dad is lagging behind.

2. Mother works without pay for the family, Dad spends all his pay for the family, both their efforts are equal, still donтАЩt know why Dad is lagging behind.

3. Mom cooks whatever you want, Dad buys whatever you want, both their love is equal, but MomтАЩs love is shown as superior. DonтАЩt know why Dad is lagging behind.

4. When you talk over the phone, you want to talk to Mom first, if you get hurt, you cry тАШMomтАЩ. You will only remember dad when you need him, but did Dad never  feels bad that you donтАЩt remember him the other times? When it comes to receiving love from children, for generations, we see that Dad is always lagging.

5.  Cupboards will be filled with colorful sarees and many clothes for kids but DadтАЩs clothes are very few, he doesnтАЩt care about his own needs, still donтАЩt know why Dad is lagging behind.

6.  Mom has many gold ornaments, but Dad has only one ring that was given during his wedding . Still Mom complaints of less jewellery and Dad doesn't. Still don't know why is Dad lagging behind.

7. Dad works very hard all his life to take care of the family, but when it comes to getting recognition, he is always lagging behind.

8. Mom says, we need to pay college tuition this month, please donтАЩt buy a saree for me for the festival whereas dad has not even thought of new clothes.Both their love is equal, still donтАЩt know why Dad is lagging behind.

9. When parents become old, children say, Mom is at least useful in taking care of household chores, but they say, Dad is useless.

Dad is *behind (or тАШat the backтАЩ )* because he is the backbone of the family. Because of him, we are able to stand erect. Probably, this is the reason why he is lagging *behind*.

Don't know how many will relate to this post and agree to this.......

Shah Rukh Khan is a college student (!) whose girlfriend is touring in China. She gets infected with coronavirus and has been quarantined in a high security hospital in China. 

When the hero hears this, he consults a local baba, who gives a special medicine, which is nothing but 'Hindustan ki mittiтАЩ (soil of mother India). 

The hero now faces several hurdles while trying to deliver this medicine to his sweetheart, like breaching the border as there is travel restriction, extreme security at the hospital and a villain trying to sabotage the mission by replacing the medicine with 'Pakistan ki mitti'. 

How the hero accomplishes his mission is rest of the story.

The title of the movie is: *CORONA PYAR HAI* !!

3/11/20, 2:04 PM - Mom: Impact of Corona virus on investment and equity markets
3/11/20, 2:07 PM - Mom: All existing visas to India suspended till April 15

Important decisions taken at the 2nd meeting of GoM on #COVID19 today.

1. All existing visas, except diplomatic, official, UN/International Organizations, employment, project visas, stand suspended till 15th April 2020. This will come into effect from 1200 GMT on 13th March 2020 at the port of departure.

2. Visa free travel facility granted to OCI card holders is kept in abeyance till April 15th 2020. This 

will come into effect from 1200 GMT on 13th March 2020 at the port of departure.

3. Any foreign national who intends to travel to India for compelling reason may contact the nearest Indian Mission.

4. All incoming travelers, including Indians, arriving from or having visited China,Italy,Iran,Republic of Korea, France, Spain & Germany after 15th Feb, 2020 shall be quarantined for a minimum period of 14 days. The above will come into effect from 1200 GMT on 13th March 2020 at the port of departure

5. Incoming travelers, including Indian nationals, are advised to avoid non-essential travel and are informed that they can be quarantined for a minimum of 14 days on their arrival in India.

6. Indian nationals are strongly advised to avoid all non-essential travel abroad. On their return, they can be subjected to quarantine for a minimum of 14 days.

7. International traffic through land borders will be restricted to Designated check posts with robust screening facilities. These will be notified separately by M/o Home Affairs.

8. Provision for testing primarily for students/compassionate cases in #Italy Italy to be made and collection for samples to be organized accordingly. Those tested negative will be allowed to travel and will be quarantined on arrival in India for 14 days.

India 

Week 1 - 3
Week 2 - 24
Week 3 - 105

Next two weeks are crucial for India.
If we take adequate precaution and break the chain then we can tide the Corona virus Outbreak else we have a big problem in hand especially for the elderly population
So far so good. India has done well so far in its fight to contain Corona Virus. Now we are in stage 3 in which Virus spreads through social contacts & in social gatherings. This is most critical stage & number of confirmed cases spread exponentially everyday like what happened in Italy between last week of February & second week of March. From 300 to 10,000. If India is not able to manage this stage for next 3 to 4 weeks then we could have confirmed cases not in Thousands but in Lakhs. This next one month is crucial. That is why most events & public gatherings have been closed till 15th April.

Just because schools are closed avoid getting that compulsive travel & Holiday bug. Holidays will come next year too why try your luck with Corona specially with children. Marriage functions, Birthday parties etc can wait. DonтАЩt try your luck & that bravado that nothing will happen to me. Next 30 days will be most crucial in medical History of India. Take all precautions while at home & while outside for any important work. Precaution is not panic.

Be a responsible citizen by following & educating others to remain careful for next one month.

*#CoronaVirus*

3/18/20, 3:50 PM - Sahil Sheth: Just received this information from ViennaтАЩs laboratory studying COVID-19 and vast majority of people who died of it, had ibuprofen in their system so do not take it!! Those who recovered did not take ibuprofen so if you have symptoms, take Paracetamol only!!! Looks like this virus thrives on ibuprofen so donтАЩt do it and tell everyone you can!!!


Do NOT take ibuprofen! 

We have just been sent a medical alert that no one is to use anti inflammatories (eg brufen, Voltarol, naproxen and there are others)  for pain or high temperature. Use paracetamol instead. There seems to be a link between severe cases of covid19 affecting young people with no underlying illnesses and taking anti inflammatories. Initial reports started coming from French Drs on Friday. This has been confirmed by infectious diseases consultants here - there are 4 young people in ICU in Cork who have no underlying illnesses - all were taking anti inflammatories and there are concerns this has caused a more severe illness. We have been asked to spread the message. French tv and radio apparently broadcast the same warning today - from pharmacy friend I know most of you work within a hospital but just incase

*тАЬWhatever we are talking about is what we are perpetuating in our experience. The only way to keep any kind of illness or virus or flu away is to not talk about it and it will dissipate itself. What we do instead is keep checking the statistics or keep spreading the "awareness" messages on social media without noticing it that the more we talk about it the more it becomes active in our vibration. History is full of evidence of epidemics because of the mass consciousness created by fear of the disease. Fear is a very strong vibration and more fearful we are of any epidemic it becomes a reality very fast.. it's the law. The more you feed the energy of fear the more profound it becomes. Ignore the things you don't want to participate in. Stop discussing it with family and friends; stop checking out the latest statistics. Stop watching incessantly the news about Corona Virus. Take your attention away and It has no power on you. The creation of anything is to give thought to it by keeping it active in our vibration by being afraid of it. Hook yourself up with  ever flowing stream of well- beingтАЭ.*

*Love and light to all.*
*Sadhguru*.

4/4/20, 11:36 PM - Mom: INDIA IS SURPRISING THE WORLD - ALL INDIANS PLEASE TAKE A BOW !
A friend of mine ,who is an NRI & whose  group has many NRIs, sent his thoughts Posted below ЁЯСЗ

I have been tracking various social media groups and Internet forums which have millions of users from all over the world. As expected, the only topic of discussion everywhere these days is: Corona.

While most of the discussions are mostly about precautions and updates, a significant number of users have also now started noticing the maturity with which India is handling this issue. What was till recently considered a third world nation, is now quickly gaining respect & recognition at the world stage. 

Following are a few examples which illustrate how India is impressing the foreigners:-

1) Firstly,  and most importantly,  many are impressed with Indian Govt's quick measures & proactive initiatives even at such initial stages- Janta Curfew, Complete 21 days Lockdown, etc... The reason for this appreciation is that in all other countries in Europe and even USA, despite the rapid rise in cases, their respective govts had been ignoring the issue, and some were even taking it casually. Whereas India is one of the very few nations where Govt has jumped into action to tackle at root level itself.  This has impressed many foreigners, especially Americans. 

2) The strong measures like strict lockdown & police bandobast in India is being specially appreciated by Europeans. The reason here is that Europe is usually a highly democratic continent where emphasis is more on giving flexibility to people. So, they find it a bit strange when they see news visuals of Indian police forcefully  chasing out violators from the streets during the curfew. In fact, Italians have been highly impressed with scenes where Indian policemen have lathi charged violators, because the Italians know the severity of this issue, and hence they feel such ruthless strictness by Indian police is fully justified, and is in the best interest of larger public.

3) Many, specially the Americans,  are impressed with the calmness of Indians, who are not resorting to crazy hoarding of essential items despite a nationwide lockdown. For example, even now, most of the American stores are almost empty, and Americans are fighting against each other in stores over these issues & are on a Gun buying spree ! However, in India, everything seems to be running smoothly without any hoarding or shortages. 

4) Almost the whole World is impressed with the innovative methods used by Indians to follow social distancing.  For example, the circles & boxes drawn using rangoli powder to ensure decent distance between people in queues at groceries, ATMs etc.... . 

5) The world is clearly noticing how Indians are utilising their skills of jugaad to solve these tough problems.  For instance, PM Modi's idea of turning train coaches into ICU wards , creating 10,000 bed mobile hospital and sending them to all parts of India over railway, has taken many by surprise, because it is so simple yet so practical.

6) Low cost kits developed by an Indian Company Mylab, Low cost ventilators developed by Mahindra company's mechanical engineers. All these show Indian engineers are also rising to the occasion to help the health sector, with these innovative & affordable solutions. Everyone from across the world have been highly appreciative of these, and are now encouraging their own engineers to follow suit. Many startupтАЩs have sprung up to invent low cost solutions.

7) Public participation in India is something which has taken everyone by surprise. Probably because the usual perception about India in the west is that Indians are illiterate, careless, selfish, lazy etc. So, when they find Indians heeding to the leader's call for participation through different means like Janata curfew, cheering for health workers etc, so enthusiastically, it gives an impression that Indians really care for their nation, are serious about fighting this issue, etc.

8) The Indian PM floated a "PM Care Fund" and both Corporates like Tata & Reliance donating Crores and Individuals also donating Crores. No other World Leader has created such a fund or companies in those countries have donated on their own.

9) Last, but not the least. Finally, India is emerging as a new powerhouse, thanks to a strong & trustworthy leadership. The clarity and focus with which Indian PM is tackling this issue seriously, has already started receiving accolades from all over the World. During this global crisis, when China is acting like a cheat, Europe is down to its knees, and America is running like a headless chicken, the words from Indian PM, in all the recent summits have been heartwarming and inspiring confidence. In some ways, PM Modi is now taking the role of a global leader and bringing accolades to India, filling the vacuum, taking charge & guiding the world, just like how leaders like Abraham Lincoln had long ago filled leadership vacuum and inspired the world. This is something which rest of the world is also beginning to notice, and acknowledging the same. 

INDIA SURE IS SURPRISING THE WORLD  !!
N
Proud to be an Indian. 
Jai Hind.

*рдЙрддреНрддрд░:-* рдХреЛрд░реЛрдирд╛ рд╡рд╛рдпрд░рд╕ рдмрд╣реБрдд рдХрдореЫреЛрд░ рд╣реЛрддрд╛ рд╣реИред *рдЗрд╕рдХреЗ рдКрдкрд░ рдЪреЭреА рдЪрд░реНрдмреА рдХреА рд╕реБрд░рдХреНрд╖рд╛-рдкрд░рдд рдлрд╛реЬ рджреЗрдиреЗ рд╕реЗ рдпрд╣ реЩрддреНрдо рд╣реЛ рдЬрд╛рддрд╛ рд╣реИред* рдРрд╕рд╛ рдХрд░рдиреЗ рдХреЗ рд▓рд┐рдпреЗ рд╕рд╛рдмреБрди рдпрд╛ рдбрд┐рдЯрд░реНрдЬреЗрдВрдЯ рдХреЗ рдЭрд╛рдЧ рд╕рдмрд╕реЗ реЫреНрдпрд╛рджрд╛ рдкреНрд░рднрд╛рд╡реА рд╣реЛрддреЗ рд╣реИрдВред *20 рд╕реЗрдХрдВрдб рдпрд╛ рдЙрд╕рд╕реЗ реЫреНрдпрд╛рджрд╛ рджреЗрд░ рддрдХ рд╕рд╛рдмреБрди/рдбрд┐рдЯрд░реНрдЬреЗрдВрдЯ рд▓рдЧрд╛рдХрд░ рд╣рд╛рдереЛрдВ рдХреЛ рд░рдЧреЬрдиреЗ рд╕реЗ рдЗрд╕рдХреА рд╕реБрд░рдХреНрд╖рд╛-рдкрд░рдд рдлрдЯ рдЬрд╛рддреА рд╣реИ* рдФрд░ рдпреЗ рдирд╖реНрдЯ рд╣реЛ рдЬрд╛рддрд╛ рд╣реИред рдЗрд╕рд▓рд┐рдпреЗ рдЕрдкрдиреЗ рд╢рд░реАрд░ рдХреЗ рдЦреБрд▓реЗ рдЕрдВрдЧреЛрдВ рдХреЛ рдмрд╛рд░-рдмрд╛рд░ рд╕рд╛рдмреБрди рд╡ рдкрд╛рдиреА рд╕реЗ рдзреЛрдирд╛ рдЪрд╛рд╣рд┐рдпреЗ, реЩрд╛рд╕ рддреМрд░ рд╕реЗ рдЙрд╕ рд╡реШреНрдд рдЬрдм рдЖрдк рдмрд╛рд╣рд░ рд╕реЗ рдШрд░ рдореЗрдВ рдЖрдП рд╣реЛрдВред

рдкреНрд░рд╢реНрди(10):-рдХрд┐рд╕ рддрд░рд╣ рдХрд╛ рдорд╛рд╣реМрд▓ рдХреЛрд░реЛрдирд╛ рд╡рд╛рдпрд░рд╕ рдХреЗ рд▓рд┐рдпреЗ рдлрд╛рдпрджреЗрдордВрдж рд╣реИ рдФрд░ рдХрд┐рд╕ рддрд░рд╣ рдХреЗ рдорд╛рд╣реМрд▓ рдореЗрдВ рд╡реЛ рдЬрд▓реНрджреА рд╡рд┐рдШрдЯрд┐рдд рд╣реЛрддрд╛ рд╣реИ?

*рдЙрддреНрддрд░:-* рдХреЛрд░реЛрдирд╛ рд╡рд╛рдпрд░рд╕ реШреБрджрд░рддреА рдардгреНрдбрдХ рдпрд╛ рдПрд╕реА рдХреА рдардгреНрдбрдХ рдореЗрдВ рдореЫрдмреВрдд рд╣реЛрддрд╛ рд╣реИред рдЗрд╕реА рддрд░рд╣ рдЕрдВрдзреЗрд░реЗ рдФрд░ рдирдореА (Moisture) рд╡рд╛рд▓реА рдЬрдЧрд╣ рдкрд░ рднреА реЫреНрдпрд╛рджрд╛ рджреЗрд░ рддрдХ рдмрд╛реШреА рд░рд╣рддрд╛ рд╣реИред рдпрд╛рдиреА рдЗрди рдЬрдЧрд╣реЛрдВ рдкрд░ реЫреНрдпрд╛рджрд╛ рджреЗрд░ рддрдХ рд╡рд┐рдШрдЯрд┐рдд рдирд╣реАрдВ рд╣реЛрддрд╛ред *рд╕реВрдЦрд╛, рдЧрд░реНрдо рдФрд░ рд░реЛрд╢рдиреА рд╡рд╛рд▓рд╛ рдорд╛рд╣реМрд▓ рдХреЛрд░реЛрдирд╛ рд╡рд╛рдпрд░рд╕ рдХреЗ рдЬрд▓реНрджреА реЩрд╛рддреНрдореЗ рдореЗрдВ рдорджрджрдЧрд╛рд░ рд╣реИред* рдЗрд╕рд▓рд┐рдП рдЬрдм рддрдХ рдЗрд╕рдХрд╛ рдкреНрд░рдХреЛрдк рд╣реИ рддрдм рддрдХ рдП.рд╕реА. рдпрд╛ рдПрдпрд░ рдХреВрд▓рд░ рдХрд╛ рдЗрд╕реНрддреЗрдорд╛рд▓ рди рдХрд░реЗрдВред

рдкреНрд░рд╢реНрди (11):- рд╕реВрд░рдЬ рдХреА рддреЗреЫ рдзреВрдк рдХрд╛ рдХреЛрд░реЛрдирд╛ рдкрд░ рдХреНрдпрд╛ рдЕрд╕рд░ рдкреЬрддрд╛ рд╣реИ?

*рдЙрддреНрддрд░:-* рд╕реВрд░рдЬ рдХреА рдзреВрдк рдореЗрдВ рдореМрдЬреВрдж *рдЕрд▓реНрдЯреНрд░рд╛рд╡рд╛рдпрд▓реЗрдЯ рдХрд┐рд░рдгреЗрдВ* рдХреЛрд░реЛрдирд╛ рд╡рд╛рдпрд░рд╕ рдХреЛ рддреЗреЫреА рд╕реЗ рд╡рд┐рдШрдЯрд┐рдд рдХрд░ рджреЗрддреА рд╣реИ рдпрд╛рдирд┐ рддреЛреЬ рджреЗрддреА рд╣реИ рдХреНрдпреЛрдВрдХрд┐ рд╕реВрд░рдЬ рдХреА рддреЗреЫ рдзреВрдк рдореЗрдВ рдЙрд╕рдХреА рд╕реБрд░рдХреНрд╖рд╛-рдкрд░рдд рдкрд┐рдШрд▓ рдЬрд╛рддреА рд╣реИред рдЗрд╕реАрд▓рд┐рдП рдЪреЗрд╣рд░реЗ рдкрд░ рд▓рдЧрд╛рдП рдЬрд╛рдиреЗ рд╡рд╛рд▓реЗ рдлреЗрд╕рдорд╛рд╕реНрдХ рдпрд╛ рд░реБрдорд╛рд▓ рдХреЛ рдЕрдЪреНрдЫреЗ рдбрд┐рдЯрд░реНрдЬреЗрдВрдЯ рд╕реЗ рдзреЛрдиреЗ рдФрд░ рддреЗреЫ рдзреВрдк рдореЗрдВ рд╕реБрдЦрд╛рдиреЗ рдХреЗ рдмрд╛рдж рджреЛрдмрд╛рд░рд╛ рдЗрд╕реНрддреЗрдорд╛рд▓ рдХрд┐рдпрд╛ рдЬрд╛ рд╕рдХрддрд╛ рд╣реИред

рдкреНрд░рд╢реНрди (12):- рдХреНрдпрд╛ рд╣рдорд╛рд░реА рдЪрдореЬреА (рддреНрд╡рдЪрд╛) рд╕реЗ рдХреЛрд░реЛрдирд╛ рд╡рд╛рдпрд░рд╕ рд╢рд░реАрд░ рдореЗрдВ рдЬрд╛ рд╕рдХрддрд╛ рд╣реИ?

*рдЙрддреНрддрд░:-* рдирд╣реАрдВ! рддрдВрджреБрд░реБрд╕реНрдд рддреНрд╡рдЪрд╛ рд╕реЗ рдХреЛрд░реЛрдирд╛ рд╕рдВрдХреНрд░рдордг рдирд╣реАрдВ рд╣реЛ рд╕рдХрддрд╛ред рдЕрдЧрд░ рддреНрд╡рдЪрд╛ рдкрд░ рдХрд╣реАрдВ рдХрдЯ рд▓рдЧрд╛ рд╣реИ рдпрд╛ рдШрд╛рд╡ рд╣реИ рддреЛ рдЗрд╕рдХреЗ рд╕рдВрдХреНрд░рдордг рдХреА рд╕рдВрднрд╛рд╡рдирд╛ рд╣реИред

рдкреНрд░рд╢реНрди (13):- рдХреНрдпрд╛ рд╕рд┐рд░рдХрд╛ рдорд┐рд▓реЗ рдкрд╛рдиреА рд╕реЗ рдХреЛрд░реЛрдирд╛ рд╡рд╛рдпрд░рд╕ рд╡рд┐рдШрдЯрд┐рдд рд╣реЛ рд╕рдХрддрд╛ рд╣реИ?*

*рдЙрддреНрддрд░:-* рдирд╣реАрдВ! рд╕рд┐рд░рдХрд╛ рдХреЛрд░реЛрдирд╛ рд╡рд╛рдпрд░рд╕ рдХреА рд╕реБрд░рдХреНрд╖рд╛-рдкрд░рдд рдХреЛ рдирд╣реАрдВ рддреЛреЬ рд╕рдХрддрд╛ред рдЗрд╕рд▓рд┐рдпреЗ рд╕рд┐рд░рдХрд╛ рд╡рд╛рд▓реЗ рдкрд╛рдиреА рд╕реЗ рд╣рд╛рде-рдореБрдБрд╣ рдзреЛрдиреЗ рд╕реЗ рдХреЛрдИ реЮрд╛рдпрджрд╛ рдирд╣реАрдВ рд╣реИред

5/14/20, 2:12 PM - +1 (626) 493-4232: ORAC





ORAC is Oxygen Radical Absorbance Capacity. Higher ORAC, Better will be oxygen carrying capacity of blood & Lungs oxygen capacity. 

In the Future, our survival will be based on our Immunity 

Why spices are important for our Life? Look at their ORAC Values....ЁЯСНЁЯЩП

Clove       : 314,446 ORAC 
Cinnamon : 267,537 ORAC 
Coffee.  : 243000  ORAC
Turmeric  : 102,700 ORAC 
Cocoa    : 80,933    ORAC 
Cumin    : 76,800  ORAC 
Parsley  : 74,349 ORAC 
Tulsi       : 67,553 ORAC 
Thyme    : 27,426ORAC

рдереЛрдбрд╝реА рджреЗрд░ рдмрд╛рдж рдкрдбрд╝реЛрд╕реА *рд░рд┐рдкреЛрд░реНрдЯ рд▓реЗ рдХрд░* рд╡рд╛рдкрд┐рд╕ рдЖрдпрд╛,

рдореБрдЭреЗ рдЪрд╛рдмреА рджреА рдФрд░ *рдореБрдЭреЗ рдЧрд▓реЗ рд▓рдЧрд╛рдпрд╛* рдФрд░ 

*"рдмрд╣реБрдд рдмрд╣реБрдд рдзрдиреНрдпрд╡рд╛рдж"* рдХрд╣рдХрд░ рдЕрдкрдиреЗ рдШрд░ рдЪрд▓рд╛ рдЧрдпрд╛ред  

рдЬреИрд╕реЗ рд╣реА рд╡рд╣ рдЕрдкрдиреЗ рдШрд░ рдЧрдпрд╛, 

рдЧреЗрдЯ рдкрд░ рд╣реА рдЦрдбреЗ рд╣реЛрдХрд░ рдЕрдкрдиреА рдкрддреНрдиреА рд╕реЗ рдХрд╣рдиреЗ рд▓рдЧрд╛..

*"рд░рд┐рдкреЛрд░реНрдЯ рдкреЙрдЬрд┐рдЯрд┐рд╡ рдЖрдпреА рд╣реИ!"* тЬФя╕П

рдЬрдм рдпрд╣ рдмрд╛рдд рдореЗрд░реЗ рдХрд╛рди рдореЗрдВ рдкрдбрд╝реА рддреЛ рдореИрдВ рддреЛ рдЧрд┐рд░рддреЗ-рдЧрд┐рд░рддреЗ рдмрдЪрд╛..

рдШрдмрд░рд╛рдХрд░ рдореИрдиреЗ рдЕрдкрдиреЗ *рд╣рд╛рде рд╕реИрдирд┐рдЯрд╛рдЗрдЬрд╝рд░ рд╕реЗ* рд╕рд╛рдлрд╝ рдХрд┐рдпреЗ,

рдлрд┐рд░ *рдмрд╛рдЗрдХ рдХреЛ* рджреЛ рдмрд╛рд░ рд╕рд░реНрдл рд╕реЗ рдзреЛрдпрд╛,

рдлрд┐рд░ рдпрд╛рдж рдЖрдпрд╛ рдЙрд╕рдиреЗрдВ рдореБрдЭреЗ *рдЧрд▓реЗ рднреА* рд▓рдЧрдпрд╛ рдерд╛,

рдореИрдВрдиреЗ рдорди рдореЗ рд╕реЛрдЪрд╛.. 
*рдорд╛рд░рд╛ рдЧрдпрд╛ рддреВ рдмреЗрдЯрд╛, рддреБрдЭреЗ рднреА рдЕрдм "рдХреЛрд░реЛрдирд╛" рд╣реЛрдЧрд╛*

рдлрд┐рд░ рдореИрдВ *рдбреЗрдЯреЛрд▓ рд╕рд╛рдмреВрди рд╕реЗ* рд░рдЧрдбрд╝-рд░рдЧрдбрд╝ рдХрд░ рдирд╣рд╛рдпрд╛ 

рдФрд░ рдмрд╛рдерд░реВрдо рдореЗрдВ рд╣реА рджреБрдГрдЦреА рд╣реЛрдХрд░ рдПрдХ рдХреЛрдиреЗ рдореЗрдВ рдмреИрда рдЧрдпрд╛ред

рдереЛрдбреА рджреЗрд░ рдмрд╛рдж рдореИрдВрдиреЗ рдкрдбрд╝реЛрд╕реА рдХреЛ рдлреЛрди рдХрд░рдХреЗ рдмреЛрд▓рд╛:

*"рднрд╛рдИ, рдЕрдЧрд░ рдЖрдкрдХреА рд░рд┐рдкреЛрд░реНрдЯ рдкреЙрдЬрд┐рдЯрд┐рд╡ рдереА, рддреЛ рдХрдо рд╕реЗ рдХрдо рдореБрдЭреЗ рддреЛ рдмрдЦреНрд╢ рджреЗрддреЗ ?"*

*"рдореИрдВ  рддреЛ рдмрдЪ рдЬрд╛рддрд╛"* ЁЯШн

рдкрдбрд╝реЛрд╕реА рдЬреЛрд░-рдЬреЛрд░ рд╕реЗ рд╣рдВрд╕рдиреЗ рд▓рдЧрд╛ рдФрд░ рдХрд╣рдиреЗ рд▓рдЧрд╛.. 

*"рд╡реЛ рд░рд┐рдкреЛрд░реНрдЯ.. ?"* ЁЯУДЁЯШЙ

6/28/20, 10:05 AM - Mom: Vanilla Ice Cream that puzzled General motorsтАЩ!!!!

An Interesting Story

Never underestimate your Clients' Complaint, no matter how funny it might
seem!

This is a real story that happened between the customer of General Motors
and its Customer-Care Executive. Please read on.

A complaint was received by the Pontiac Division of General Motors:

'This is the second time I have written to you, and I don't blame you for not answering me, because I sounded crazy, but it is a fact that we have a tradition in our family of Ice-Cream for dessert after dinner each night,
but the kind of ice cream varies so, every night, after we've eaten, the whole family votes on which kind of ice cream we should have and I drive down to the store to get it. It's also a fact that I recently purchased a new Pontiac and since then my trips to the store have created a
problem.

You see, every time I buy a vanilla ice-cream, when I start back from the store my car won't start. If I get any other kind of ice cream, the car starts just fine. I want you to know I'm serious about this question, no
matter how silly it sounds "What is there about a Pontiac that makes it not start when I get vanilla ice cream, and easy to start whenever I get any
other kind?" The Pontiac President was understandably skeptical about the letter, but sent an Engineer to check it out anyway.

The latter was surprised to be greeted by a successful, obviously well educated man in a fine neighborhood. He had arranged to meet the man just
after dinner time, so the two hopped into the car and drove to the ice cream store. It was vanilla ice cream that night and, sure enough, after they came back to the car, it wouldn't start.

The Engineer returned for three more nights. The first night, they got chocolate. The car started. The second night, he got strawberry. The car started. The third night he ordered vanilla. The car failed to start.

Now the engineer, being a logical man, refused to believe that this man's car was allergic to vanilla ice cream. He arranged, therefore, to continue
his visits for as long as it took to solve the problem. And toward this end he began to take notes: He jotted down all sorts of data: time of day, type of gas uses, time to drive back and forth etc.

In a short time, he had a clue: the man took less time to buy vanilla than any other flavor. Why? The answer was in the layout of the store. Vanilla,
being the most popular flavor, was in a separate case at the front of the store for quick pickup. All the other flavors were kept in the back of the store at a different counter where it took considerably longer to check out
the flavor.

Now, the question for the Engineer was why the car wouldn't start when it took less time. E..ureka - Time was now the problem - not the vanilla ice
cream!!!! The engineer quickly came up with the answer: "vapor lock".

It was happening every night; but the extra time taken to get the other flavors allowed the engine to cool down sufficiently to start. When the man got vanilla, the engine was still too hot for the vapor lock to dissipate.

Even crazy looking problems are sometimes real and all problems seem to be simple only when we find the solution, with cool thinking.

Don't just say it is " IMPOSSIBLE" without putting a sincere effort.
What really matters is your attitude and your perception.

Moral of the Story: "Try to Fix the Bug instead of making it as a known issue."
Worth reading

     рдЬреНрдпрд╛рд░реЗ рдЖрдкрдгреЗ рдкрдг рдорд╛рд▓рд╛ рдХрд░реАрдП рдЫреАрдП рдЕрдиреЗ рдЕрд╖реНрдЯрд╛рдХреНрд╖рд░ рдордВрддреНрд░рдиреЛ рдЬрдк рдХрд░реАрдП рдЫреАрдП рддреНрдпрд╛рд░реЗ рдорд╛рддреНрд░ рдЕрд╖реНрдЯрд╛рдХреНрд╖рд░ рдордВрддреНрд░ рдЬрдкрддрд╛ рдирдереА, рдЖрдкрдгреЗ рддреЛ рдП рдПрдХ рдПрдХ рдирд┐рдХреБрдВрдЬрдорд╛рдВ рдмреЗрдареЗрд▓реА рд╕рдЦреАрдиреА рд╕рд╛рдереЗ рдЖрддреНрдорд╕рд╛рдд рдХрд░реАрдП рдЫреАрдП. рдП рдордгрдХрд╛рдиреЗ рдлреЗрд░рд╡рддрд╛рдВ рдлреЗрд░рд╡рддрд╛рдВ рдЬреЗ рдордгрдХрд╛рдиреА рдЕрдВрджрд░ рдЖрдкрдгреА рдирд┐рдХреБрдВрдЬ рд╣реЛрдп, рдПрдорд╛рдВ рдмреЗрдареЗрд▓реА рд╕рдЦреАрдиреА рд╕рд╛рдереЗ рдЖрдкрдгреЛ рдЖрддреНрдорд╕рд╛рдд рдердЗ рдЬрд╛рдп, рддреНрдпрд╛рд░реЗ рдЖрдкрдгрдиреЗ рд╢реНрд░реАрдард╛рдХреЛрд░рдЬреАрдиреА рд▓реАрд▓рд╛рдиреЛ рдЕрдиреБрднрд╡ рдерд╛рдп рдЫреЗ, рддреНрдпрд╛рд░реЗ рд╢реНрд░реАрдард╛рдХреЛрд░рдЬреА рдЖрдкрдгрдиреЗ рдП рдкрд░рдо рд╕реМрднрд╛рдЧреНрдпрдиреБрдВ рджрд╛рди рдЖрдкреЗ рдЫреЗ.

ркЖрккркгрк╛ркорк╛ркВркирк╛ ркорлЛркЯрк╛ ркнрк╛ркЧркирк╛ рк▓рлЛркХрлЛ рккркг ркерлЛркбрк╛ ркЕркВрк╢рлЗ рккрлЗрк▓рк╛ ркорк╛ркгрк╕ ркЬрлЗрк╡рк╛ рк╣рлЛркИркП ркЫрлАркП. ркЬрлЗ ркХркВркИ ркЖрккркгрлА рккрк╛рк╕рлЗ ркЫрлЗ, ркПркорк╛ркВркерлА ркЭрк╛ркЭрлБркВ рк╕рлБркЦ ркиркерлА ркорк│ркдрлБркВ. рккркг рккркЫрлА ркП ркЦрлЛрк╡рк╛ркИ ркЧркпрк╛ ркмрк╛ркж рккрк╛ркЫрлБркВ ркорк│рлЗ ркдрлНркпрк╛рк░рлЗ рк╕рк╛рк░рлБркВ рк▓рк╛ркЧрлЗ.

ркЖрк╡рлБркВ рк╢рк╛ ркорк╛ркЯрлЗ?

ркПркЯрк▓рлЗ, рк╣рк╡рлЗ рккркЫрлА ркЬрлНркпрк╛рк░рлЗ ркорлВркб рк╕рк╛рк░рлЛ рки рк╣рлЛркп, ркдрлНркпрк╛рк░рлЗ ркШрк░ркорк╛ркВркирлА ркмркзрлА рк╡рк╕рлНркдрлБркУркирлЗ рк╢рк╛ркВркдрк┐ркерлА ркирлАрк░ркЦрк╡рлА ркЕркирлЗ рккркЫрлА рк╡рк┐ркЪрк╛рк░рк╡рлБркВ ркХрлЗ ркЖ рк╡рк╕рлНркдрлБ ркЬрлЛ ркорк╛рк░рлА рккрк╛рк╕рлЗ рки рк╣рлЛркп ркдрлЛ ркХрлЗркЯрк▓рлА ркдркХрк▓рлАркл рккркбрлЗ?

ркХркбркХркбркдрлА ркаркВркбрлАркорк╛ркВ ркПркХ ркЕркдрлНркпркВркд ркЧрк░рлАркм ркорк╛ркдрк╛ рккрлЛркдрк╛ркирк╛ркВ ркмрк╛рк│ркХрлЛркирк╛ рк╢рк░рлАрк░ рккрк░ ркЫрк╛рккрк╛ркВ рккрк╛ркерк░рлА ркПркирк╛ рккрк░ ркШрк╛рк╕ тАШркУркврк╛ркбрлАтАЩркирлЗ рк╕рлВрк╡ркбрк╛рк╡рлА рк░рк╣рлА рк╣ркдрлА, ркдрлНркпрк╛рк░рлЗ ркПркирк╛ ркЯрлЗркгрк┐ркпрк╛ ркжрлАркХрк░рк╛ркП ркнрк╛ркИркирлЗ рккрлВркЫрлНркпрлБркВ, тАШрк╣рлЗркВ ркнрк╛ркИ? ркЬрлЗ рк▓рлЛркХрлЛ рккрк╛рк╕рлЗ ркЫрк╛рккрк╛ркВ ркЕркирлЗ ркШрк╛рк╕ ркирк╣рлАркВ рк╣рлЛркп ркПркоркирлА ркХрлЗрк╡рлА ркЦрк░рк╛ркм рк╣рк╛рк▓ркд ркеркдрлА рк╣рк╢рлЗ?тАЩ

ркЖрккркгрлА рккрк╛рк╕рлЗ ркШрк╛рк╕ ркЕркирлЗ ркЫрк╛рккрк╛ркВркерлА ркдрлЛ ркШркгрлА рк╕рк╛рк░рлА рк╡рк╕рлНркдрлБркУ ркШрк░ркорк╛ркВ рк╣рлЛркп ркЫрлЗ, ркПркЯрк▓рлЗ рк╣рк╡рлЗ ркХрлНркпрк╛рк░рлЗркХ тАШрк╣рлБркВ рк╕рлБркЦрлА ркиркерлА... ркорк╛рк░рлА рккрк╛рк╕рлЗ ркЖ ркиркерлА... ркорк╛рк░рлА рккрк╛рк╕рлЗ ркдрлЗ ркиркерлА... ркПрк╡рлБркВ рк▓рк╛ркЧрлЗ ркдрлНркпрк╛рк░рлЗ ркПркХ ркиркЬрк░ ркЬрлЗ ркХркВркИ ркЖрккркгрлА рккрк╛рк╕рлЗ ркЫрлЗ ркдрлЗркирк╛ рккрк░ ркирк╛ркЦрлА ркЬрлЛрк╡рлА.

ркЬрлЗрко ркХрлЗ, ркЖрк╡рлЛ рк╕рк░рк╕ ркоркЬрк╛ркирлЛ рк▓рлЗркЦ ркдркорлЗ ркУркирк▓рк╛ркЗрки рк╡рк╛ркВркЪрлА рк╢ркХрлЛ ркЫрлЛ, ркдрлЗркирк╛ рккрк░ркерлА ркЖркЯрк▓рлА ркмрк╛ркмркд рк╕рк╛ркмрк┐ркд ркерк╛ркп ркЫрлЗ- 

01. ркдркорлЗ ркЧрк░рлАркм ркиркерлА. (рк╕ркоркЧрлНрк░ рк╡рк┐рк╢рлНрк╡ркорк╛ркВ ркЖрк╢рк░рлЗ 112 ркХрк░рлЛркб рк▓рлЛркХрлЛ ркЧрк░рлАркмрлА рк░рлЗркЦрк╛ ркирлАркЪрлЗ ркЬрлАрк╡рлЗ ркЫрлЗ.)

02. ркдркорк╛рк░рлА ркЬрк╛ркдркирлЗ ркаркВркбрлА, ркЧрк░ркорлА ркЕркирлЗ рк╡рк░рк╕рк╛ркж рк╕рк╛ркорлЗ рк░ркХрлНрк╖ркг ркЖрккрк╡рк╛ ркЖрк╢рк░рлЛ ркЫрлЗ ркЬрлЗ рк╡рк┐рк╢рлНрк╡ркорк╛ркВ рк▓ркЧркнркЧ 130 ркХрк░рлЛркб рк▓рлЛркХрлЛ рккрк╛рк╕рлЗ ркиркерлА.

03. ркдркорлЗ рк╢рк╛ркВркдрк┐ркерлА ркмрлЗрк╕рлАркирлЗ рк╡рк╛ркВркЪрлА рк╢ркХрлЛ ркЫрлЛ, ркоркдрк▓ркм ркХрлЗ ркдркорлЗ ркЕркдрлНркпркВркд ркорк╛ркВркжрк╛ ркиркерлА. (ркжрлБркирк┐ркпрк╛ркорк╛ркВ ркХрлЛркИ рккркг рк╕ркоркпрлЗ ркЖрк╢рк░рлЗ 120 ркХрк░рлЛркб рк▓рлЛркХрлЛ ркмрлАркорк╛рк░ рк╣рлЛркп ркЫрлЗ)

04. ркдркорк╛рк░рлА рккрк╛рк╕рлЗ ркЖркЯрк▓рлЛ рк╕рк╛рк░рлЛ ркорлЛркмрк╛ркЗрк▓ ркЫрлЗ ркЬрлЗ ркжрлБркирк┐ркпрк╛ркирк╛ 198 ркХрк░рлЛркб рк▓рлЛркХрлЛ рккрк╛рк╕рлЗ ркиркерлА.

05. ркдркоркирлЗ рккрлАрк╡рк╛ркирлБркВ рккрк╛ркгрлА ркШрлЗрк░ ркмрлЗркарк╛ ркорк│рлА рк░рк╣рлЗркдрлБркВ рк╣рк╢рлЗ, ркЬрлЗ рк╡рк┐рк╢рлНрк╡ркорк╛ркВ ркЖрк╢рк░рлЗ 180 ркХрк░рлЛркб рк▓рлЛркХрлЛркирлЗ ркиркерлА ркорк│ркдрлБркВ.

06. ркдркорк╛рк░рк╛ ркШрлЗрк░ рк╡рлАркЬрк│рлА рк╣рк╢рлЗ, (ркорлЛркмрк╛ркЗрк▓ charging ркдрлЛ ркЬ ркеркдрлБ рк╣рлЛркп ркирлЗ) ркЬрлЗ ркЬркЧркдркирк╛ 18 ркХрк░рлЛркб ркШрк░ркорк╛ркВ ркиркерлА.

07. ркдркорлЗ ркорлЛркЬркерлА ркЬрлАрк╡рк╡рк╛ рк╡рк╛рк│рк╛ рк╡рлНркпркХрлНркдрк┐ ркЫрлЛ, ркПркЯрк▓рлЗ ркЬ ркдрлЛ ркорлЛркЬ ркерлА рк╕рлБркдрк╛ ркЫрлЛ.. ркЕркирлЗ ркЬрлЛ ркмрлЗркарк╛ рк╣рк╢рлЛ ркдрлЛ рккркЧ ркЙрккрк░ рккркЧ ркЪркбрк╛рк╡рлАркирлЗ ркмрлЗркарк╛ рк╣рк╢рлЛ. ркЖрк╡рлА ркирк┐рк░рк╛ркВркд ркжрлБркирк┐ркпрк╛ркирк╛ ркЕркирлЗркХ ркХрк░рлЛркбрлЛрккркдрк┐ рккрк╛рк╕рлЗ рккркг ркиркерлА.

08. ркЖркЬ рк╕рк╡рк╛рк░рлЗ ркдркорлЗ ркЙркарлНркпрк╛ ркдрлНркпрк╛рк░рлЗ рк╡рк┐рк╢рлНрк╡ркирк╛ 88,400 рк▓рлЛркХрлЛ рккрлЛркдрк╛ркирлА ркКркВркШркорк╛ркВ ркЬ ркорлГркдрлНркпрлБ рккрк╛ркорлНркпрк╛. ркЖрк╡рлБ ркжрк░рк░рлЛркЬ ркмркирлЗ ркЫрлЗ.

ркЖркЯрк▓рлЛ ркорк╕рлНркд рк▓рлЗркЦ ркдркорлЗ ркЕркдрлНркпрк╛рк░рлЗ рк╡рк╛ркВркЪрлА рк░рк╣рлНркпрк╛ ркЫрлЛ, ркдрлЛ рккркЫрлА ркЫрлЛркбрлЛ рклрк░рк┐ркпрк╛ркжрлЛ, ркЕркирлЗ ркЖркнрк╛рк░ ркорк╛ркирлЛ ркИрк╢рлНрк╡рк░ркирлЛ, ркирк╕рлАркмркирлЛ, рккрлБрк░рлБрк╖рк╛рк░рлНркеркирлЛ ркХрлЗ, ркЬрлАрк╡рки ркорк╕рлНркд ркЫрлЗ. рк╕рк╡рк╛рк░рлЗ ркКркарлАркирлЗ ркЖрккркгрлЛ рккрлНрк░ркерко рк╢ркмрлНркж ркХркпрлЛ рк╣рлЛрк╡рлЛ ркЬрлЛркИркП ркЦркмрк░ ркЫрлЗ? ЁЯШЬЁЯШЬЁЯШЬ ... 

A young boy goes off to college. Half way through the semester, having foolishly squandered all his money ... he calls home.

"Dad" he says, "You won't believe what modern education is developing!
They actually have a program here in our institution that will teach our dog,Jack, how to talk!"

"That's amazing,"his father says. "How do I get Jack in that program?"

"Just send him down here with $10,000" the young boy says " and I'll get him in the course."

So his father sends the dog and$10,000. About two-thirds of the way through the semester, the money again runs out. 

The boy calls home.

"So how's Jack doing son?" his father asks.

"Awesome, dad, he's talking up a storm," he says, "but you just won't believe this -- they've had such good results they have started to teach the animals how to read!"

"Read ??"says his father.

"No kidding! How do we get Jack in that program?"

"Just send $20,000, I'll get him in the class."

The money promptly arrives. But our hero has a problem.

At the end of the year, his father will find out the dog can neither talk, nor read. 

So he shoots the dog!!!

When he arrives home at the end of the year, his father is all excited.

"Where's Jack? I just can't wait to see him read something and talk!"

"Dad" the boy says, "I have some grim news.  Yesterday morning, just before we left to drive home, Jack was in the living room, kicked back in the recliner, reading The Economic Times, like he usually does. Then Jack turned to me and asked, "So, is your father still having an affair with that pretty lady RachelЁЯТГwho lives down the street ?"

The father went white and exclaimed ... "I hope you shot that son of a bitch before he talks to your Mother!"ЁЯШб

"I sure did, dad!

"That's my boy!"

The kid went on to law school and is now a politician.

рд╢реНрд░реА рдЧреЛрдкреАрдирд╛рдердЬреА - рдЬреАрд╡рди рдЪрд░рд┐рддреНрд░

рд╢реНрд░реА рдорд╣рд╛рдкреНрд░рднреБрдЬреА рдХреЗ рдЬреНрдпреЗрд╖реНрда рдкреБрддреНрд░ рд╢реНрд░реА рдЧреЛрдкреАрдирд╛рдердЬреА рдХрд╛ рдкреНрд░рд╛рдХрдЯреНрдп рд╡рд┐рдХреНрд░рдорд╛рдмреНрдж резрелремрен рдореЗрдВ рдЖрдЬ рдХреЗ рджрд┐рди рдкреНрд░рдпрд╛рдЧ (рдЗрд▓рд╛рд╣рдмрд╛рдж) рдХреЗ рдирд┐рдХрдЯ рдЕрдбреЗрд▓ рдореЗрдВ рд╣реБрдЖ рдерд╛. рдЙрдирдХреЗ рдЬрдиреНрдо рдкрд░ рд╕рднреА рдХреЛ рдЕрдкрд╛рд░ рдЖрдирдВрдж рдЕрдиреБрднрд╡ рд╣реБрдЖ рдЕрддрдГ рдорд╣рд╛рдкреНрд░рднреБрдЬреА рдиреЗ рдмреНрд░рд╛рд╣реНрдордгреЛрдВ, рдпрд╛рдЪрдХреЛрдВ, рдЧрд░реАрдмреЛрдВ рдХреЛ рдЦреВрдм рджрд╛рди-рджрдХреНрд╖рд┐рдгрд╛ рджреА рдереА.

7 рд╡рд░реНрд╖ рдХреА рдЖрдпреБ рдореЗрдВ рдЖрдкрдХрд╛ рдпрдЬреНрдЮреЛрдкрд╡реАрдд рд╕рдВрд╕реНрдХрд╛рд░ рдХрд░ рд╕реНрд╡рдпрдВ рдорд╣рд╛рдкреНрд░рднреБрдЬреА рдиреЗ рдЖрдкрдХреЛ рд╡рд┐рджреНрдпрд╛рднреНрдпрд╛рд╕ рдкреНрд░рд╛рд░рдВрдн рдХрд░рд╛рдпрд╛. рдЖрдк рдкрд░ рдорд╣рд╛рдкреНрд░рднреБрдЬреА рдХреА рд╡рд┐рджреНрд╡рддрд╛ рдПрд╡рдВ рдЕрдирдиреНрдп рднрдХреНрддрд┐ рдХрд╛ рдмрд╣реБрдд рдкреНрд░рднрд╛рд╡ рдкреЬрд╛.

рдорд╣рд╛рдкреНрд░рднреБрдЬреА рдкреНрд░рддрд┐рджрд┐рди рд╢реНрд░реАрдорджреНрднрд╛рдЧрд╡рдд рдХрд╛ рдкрд░рд╛рдпрдг рдХрд░рддреЗ. рдЙрдиреНрд╣реЗрдВ рджреЗрдЦрдХрд░ рдЖрдкрдиреЗ рднреА рдмрд╛рд▓реНрдпрд╛рд╡рд╕реНрдерд╛ рдореЗрдВ рд╣реА рд╢реНрд░реАрдорджреНрднрд╛рдЧрд╡рдд рдХрд╛ рдкрд░рд╛рдпрдг рдХрд░рдиреЗ рдХреЗ рдкрд╢реНрдЪрд╛рдд рд╣реА рднреЛрдЬрди рдЧреНрд░рд╣рдг рдХрд░рдиреЗ рдХрд╛ рдирд┐рдпрдо рд▓рд┐рдпрд╛ рдЬрд┐рд╕рдХреЗ рдкрд░рд┐рдгрд╛рдорд╕реНрд╡рд░реВрдк рдХрднреА-рдХрднреА рд╡реЗ рддреАрди-рдЪрд╛рд░ рджрд┐рд╡рд╕ рдмрд┐рдирд╛ рднреЛрдЬрди рдХреЗ рднрд╛рдЧрд╡рдд рдкрд░рд╛рдпрдг рдХрд░рддреЗ рд░рд╣рддреЗ.

рдЗрд╕рд╕реЗ рд╡реНрдпрдерд┐рдд рдЖрдкрдХреА рдорд╛рддрд╛рд╢реНрд░реА рдХреЛ рджреЗрдЦ рд╢реНрд░реА рдорд╣рд╛рдкреНрд░рднреБрдЬреА рдиреЗ рд╢реНрд░реАрдорджреНрднрд╛рдЧрд╡рдд рд╕рд╛рд░рд░реВрдк тАШрд╢реНрд░реА рдкреБрд░реБрд╖реЛрддреНрддрдо рд╕рд╣рд╕реНрддреНрд░рдирд╛рдотАЩ рдирд╛рдордХ рдЧреНрд░рдиреНрде рдХреА рд░рдЪрдирд╛ рдХреА рдПрд╡рдВ рдЧреЛрдкреАрдирд╛рдердЬреА рдХреЛ рдЧреНрд░рдиреНрде рджреЗ рдХрд░ рдЖрдЬреНрдЮрд╛ рдХреА рдХрд┐ рддреБрдо рдкреНрд░рддрд┐рджрд┐рди рдЗрд╕ рдЧреНрд░рдиреНрде рдХрд╛ рдкрд╛рда рдХрд░реЛ рдПрд╡рдВ рдЗрд╕рд╕реЗ рд╢реНрд░реАрдорджрднрд╛рдЧрд╡рдд рдХреЗ рдкрд╛рда рдХрд╛ рдлрд▓ рдорд┐рд▓реЗрдЧрд╛.

рд╢реНрд░реА рдорд╣рд╛рдкреНрд░рднреБрдЬреА рдиреЗ рдЖрд╕реБрд░рд╡реНрдпрд╛рдореЛрд╣ рд▓реАрд▓рд╛ рдХреА рддрдм рдЖрдкрдХреА рдЖрдпреБ 19 рд╡рд░реНрд╖ рдереА. рдЗрд╕ рдЕрд▓реНрдкрд╛рдпреБ рдореЗрдВ рдЖрдкрдХреЛ рдЖрдЪрд╛рд░реНрдп рдкрдж рдкреНрд░рд╛рдкреНрдд рд╣реБрдЖ.

рдЖрдкрдХреА рдмрд╣реВрдЬреА рдХрд╛ рдирд╛рдо рдкрдпрд╛рдореНрдорд╛ рдЬреА рдерд╛. рдЖрдкрдХреЛ рдкреБрд░реБрд╖реЛрддреНрддрдордЬреА рдирд╛рдо рдХреЗ рдПрдХ рдкреБрддреНрд░, рд▓рдХреНрд╖реНрдореА рдФрд░ рд╕рддреНрдпрднрд╛рдорд╛ рдирд╛рдо рдХреА рджреЛ рдкреБрддреНрд░рд┐рдпрд╛рдБ рд╣реБрдИ.

рдЖрдк рд╢рд╛рдВрдд рдПрд╡рдВ рдЧрдВрднреАрд░ рдкреНрд░рд╡реГрддрд┐ рдХреЗ рд╡рд┐рджреНрд╡рд╛рди рдереЗ. рдЖрдкрдХреА рд░реВрдЪрд┐ рдЧреНрд░рдВрдереЛрдВ рдХреЗ рдЕрднреНрдпрд╛рд╕ рдПрд╡рдВ рддреАрд░реНрдердпрд╛рддреНрд░рд╛ рдореЗрдВ рд╡рд┐рд╢реЗрд╖ рд░реВрдк рд╕реЗ рдереА. рдЖрдк рдХрдИ рдмрд╛рд░ рдЬрдЧрдиреНрдирд╛рдердкреБрд░реА рдПрд╡рдВ рджреНрд╡рд╛рд░рдХрд╛ рдХреА рдпрд╛рддреНрд░рд╛ рдХреЛ рдкрдзрд╛рд░рддреЗ рдереЗ.

9/17/20, 11:23 AM - Mom: *Corporate Joke*

Once a man goes to a shop to buy parrot. 
He asks the shop owner price of the Parrot: 

Shop owner: Rs. 500

Customer: Why so costly?
 
Shop owner: He knows, *Word, Excel and Power Point*

Customer: What's the price of this second Parrot? 

Shop owner:  Rs. 1000  
as it knows *Word, Excel, Power Point and also Programming*

Customer: How nice and what's the price of this parrot, which is sleeping?

Shop owner: That's for Rs. 5000

Customer: And what does it know?

Shop owner: That I don't know, I haven't seen him do anything, *but the other two parrots call him boss*.

*ркЖрккркгрлБ рк▓рк┐рк╡рк░ рккрк╛ркЪрки ркорк╛ркЯрлЗ рккрк┐ркд (bile) ркмркирк╛рк╡рлЗ ркЫрлЗ, ркЖрккркгрлБркВ рккрлЗркЯ ркПрк╕рк┐ркб (hydrochloric acid) ркмркирк╛рк╡рлЗ ркЫрлЗ ркЕркирлЗ ркЖрккркгрлБркВ рк╕рлНрк╡рк╛ркжрлБрккрк┐ркВркб (рккрлЗркирлНркХрлНрк░рк┐ркЖрк╕) рк╕рлНрк╡рк╛ркжрлБрккрк┐ркВркб-рк░рк╕ (pancreatic juice) ркмркирк╛рк╡рлЗ ркЫрлЗ*

рдпрд╣ рд╡реНрд░рддрдЪрд░реНрдпрд╛ рдЪреАрд░рд╣рд░рдг рд▓реАрд▓рд╛ рдХрд╛ рдорд╣рд╛рди рдЖрдзрд┐рджреИрд╡рд┐рдХ рд░рд╣рд╕реНрдп рд╣реИ ред рдЗрд╕ рдЪреАрд░рд╣рд░рдг рд▓реАрд▓рд╛ рджреНрд╡рд╛рд░рд╛ рд╣реА рдХреБрдорд╛рд░рд┐рдХрд╛рдУрдВ рдХреЗ рд╕рд░реНрд╡ рджреЛрд╖ рдХреА рдирд┐рд╡реГрддреНрддрд┐ рдХрд░ рдХреЗ рдорд╣рд╛рд░рд╛рд╕ рд░реБрдкреА рдорд╣рд╛рдлрд▓ рдХреЗ рд▓рд┐рдП рдкреНрд░рднреБ рджреНрд╡рд╛рд░рд╛ рдХреБрдорд╛рд░рд┐рдХрд╛рдУрдВ рдХрд╛ рд╕рдВрд╕реНрдХрд╛рд░ рд╣реБрдЖ рд╣реИред

рд╡реНрд░рддрдЪрд░реНрдпрд╛ рдореЗрдВ рдХреБрдорд╛рд░рд┐рдХрд╛рдУрдВ рджреНрд╡рд╛рд░рд╛ рдХрд╛рддреНрдпрд╛рдпрдиреА рджреЗрд╡реА рдХреА рдкреВрдЬрд╛, рдЕрд░реНрдЪрдирд╛, рдЬрдк рдЗрддреНрдпрд╛рджрд┐ рдХрд┐рдП рдЬрд╛рддреЗ рд╣реИрдВ, рдлрд┐рд░ рднреА рдЙрд╕рдореЗрдВ рдЕрдиреНрдпрд╛рд╢реНрд░рдп рдХрд╛ рджреЛрд╖ рдирд╣реАрдВ рд▓рдЧрддрд╛ ред рдХреНрдпреЛрдВрдХрд┐ 'рдХрд╛рддреНрдпрд╛' рдХрд╛ рдЕрд░реНрде рд╢реНрд░реА рдпрдореБрдирд╛рдЬреА рдХреА рдХреГрдкрд╛ рд╢рдХреНрддрд┐ рдЬреЛ рдХрд╛рдпрд╛ рдХрд╛ рддреНрдпрд╛рдЧ рдХрд░рд╛рдпреЗ рдФрд░ рднрдХреНрддрд┐ рдХреЗ рдмрд╛рдзрдХ рддрддреНрд╡реЛрдВ рдХрд╛ рдирд╛рд╢ рдХрд░ рдкреНрд░реЗрдо рднрдХреНрддрд┐ рдХрд╛ рдЕрдзрд┐рдХрд╛рд░ рд╕рдореНрдкрд╛рджрди рдХрд░рд╛рдиреЗ рд╡рд╛рд▓реА рд╕рдВрд╣рд╛рд░рд┐рдХрд╛ рд╢рдХреНрддрд┐ рд╣реИ ред рдкреНрд░рднреБ рдкреНрд░рд╛рдкреНрддрд┐ рдореЗрдВ рдЖрддреЗ рдЖрдзрд┐рджреИрд╡рд┐рдХ рдкреНрд░рддрд┐рдмрджреНрдз рдХреЛ рджреВрд░ рдХрд░рдиреЗ рдХрд╛ рд╕рд╛рдорд░реНрдереНрдп рджреЗрд╡реА рдХрд╛рддреНрдпрд╛рдпрдиреА рдореЗрдВ рд╣реИ, рдЗрд╕ рд▓рд┐рдП рдХрд╛рддреНрдпрд╛рдпрдиреА рджреЗрд╡реА рдХрд╛ рдкреВрдЬрди, рдордВрддреНрд░ рдЬрд╛рдк рдХрд┐рдП рдЬрд╛рддреЗ рд╣реИрдВ ред

рдЗрд╕ рд╡реНрд░рдд рдореЗрдВ рд╕рд╡реЗрд░реЗ рдЬрд▓реНрджреА рдЙрда рдХрд░ рдкреНрд░рднреБ рдХреЗ рдЧреБрдгрдЧрд╛рди рдХреЗ рд╕рд╛рде рд╢реНрд░реА рдпрдореБрдирд╛рдЬреА рдореЗрдВ рд╕реНрдирд╛рди рдХрд░рддреЗ рд╣реА рд╢реНрд░реА рдпрдореБрдирд╛рдЬреА рдиреЗ рдХреБрдорд╛рд░рд┐рдХрд╛рдУрдВ рдХреЗ рддреАрди рджреЛрд╖ рдХреЛ рджреВрд░ рдХрд┐рдпрд╛ :

рез) рдХрд╛рд▓ рдЬрдирд┐рдд рджреЛрд╖ рджреВрд░ рдХрд┐рдП,
реи) рдЕрдиреНрдп рддреАрди рд▓реЛрдХ рдХреЗ рдХреНрд▓реЗрд╢ рджреВрд░ рдХрд┐рдП,
рей) рдкреНрд░рднреБ рдХреЗ рд╕рд╛рде рдХреЗ рдорд╛рди рд▓реАрд▓рд╛ рд╕реЗ рдорд┐рд▓рдиреЗ рд╡рд╛рд▓реЗ рдкреНрд░рдгрдп рдХрд▓рд╣ рдХреЛ рднреА рджреВрд░ рдХрд┐рдпрд╛ ред

рд╕рдм рдХреБрдорд╛рд░рд┐рдХрд╛рдПрдВ рд╕реНрдирд╛рди рдХрд░рдиреЗ рдХреЗ рдкрд╢реНрдЪрд╛рдд рдХрд╛рддреНрдпрд╛рдпрдиреА рджреЗрд╡реА рдХрд╛ рдкреВрдЬрди, рдЕрд░реНрдЪрди, рдЬрдк рдХрд░рддреЗ рд╕рдордп рдПрдХ рдордВрддреНрд░ рдХрд╛ рдЙрдЪреНрдЪрд╛рд░рдг рдХрд░рддреА :тАУ

"рдХрд╛рддреНрдпрд╛рдпрдиреА рдорд╣рд╛рднрд╛рдЧреЗ рдорд╣рд╛рдпреЛрдЧрд┐рдиреНрдпрдзреАрд╢реНрд╡рд░реА ред
рдирдВрдж рдЧреЛрдк рд╕реБрддрдореН рджреЗрд╡реА рдкрддрд┐рдВ рдореЗрдВ рдХреБрд░реВрддреЗ рдирдордГ рее"

рднрд╛рд╡рд╛рд░реНрде : 
рд╣реЗ рдХрд╛рддреНрдпрд╛рдпрдиреА рджреЗрд╡реА ! рд╣реЗ рдорд╣рд╛рднрд╛рдЧрд╛ ред рдЖрдк, рдирдВрджрдЧреЛрдк рдХреЗ рдкреБрддреНрд░ рдХреЛ рд╣рдорд╛рд░реЗ рдкрддрд┐ рдХрд░реЗрдВ, рд╣рдо рдЖрдк рдХреЛ рдирдорд╕реНрдХрд╛рд░ рдХрд░рддреЗ рд╣реИрдВ ред

рдЬреИрд╕реЗ рдЛрд╖рд┐ рдЧрдг рд╕реНрд╡рдпрдВ рдордВрддреНрд░рджреНрд░рд╖реНрдЯрд╛ рд╣реИрдВ, рд╡реИрд╕реЗ рд╣реА рдпрд╣ рдЛрд╖рд┐рд░реВрдкрд╛ рдХреБрдорд╛рд░рд┐рдХрд╛рдПрдВ рд╕реНрд╡рдпрдВ рдХрд╛рддреНрдпрд╛рдпрдиреА рджреЗрд╡реА рдХреЗ рд╡реНрд░рдд рдХреЗ рдордВрддреНрд░рджреНрд░рд╖реНрдЯрд╛ рд╣реИрдВ ред

рдХрд╛рд░реНрддрд┐рдХ рдорд╛рд╕ рдХреА рдкреВрд░реНрдгрд┐рдорд╛ рд╕реЗ рдорд╛рд░реНрдЧрд╢реАрд░реНрд╖ рдорд╛рд╕ рдХреА рдкреВрд░реНрдгрд┐рдорд╛ рддрдХ рдХреБрдорд╛рд░рд┐рдХрд╛рдУрдВ рдиреЗ рд╡реНрд░рдд рдХрд┐рдпрд╛ ред рдЙрд╕рдореЗрдВ рдХрд┐рдпреЗ рдЧрдП рдореБрдЦреНрдп рдкреНрд░рднреБ рдХреЗ рдЧреБрдгрдЧрд╛рди, рдкреВрдЬрд╛, рдЕрд░реНрдЪрдирд╛, рдЬрд╛рдк рдордВрддреНрд░ рдХреЗ рджреНрд╡рд╛рд░рд╛ рдХреБрдорд╛рд░рд┐рдХрд╛рдУрдВ рдХреА рдорд╣рд╛рди рдЗрдЪреНрдЫрд╛ рдЬрд╛рди рдХрд░ рдкреНрд░рднреБ рд╡рд╣рд╛рдВ рдкрдзрд╛рд░реЗ рдФрд░ тАШрдЪреАрд░рдШрд╛рдЯтАЩ рдкрд░ тАШрдХрджрдореНрдм рд╡реГрдХреНрд╖тАЩ рдкрд░ рдмрд┐рд░рд╛рдЬрдорд╛рди рд╣реБрдП, рдФрд░ рдХреБрдорд╛рд░рд┐рдХрд╛рдУрдВ рдЕрднреАрд╖реНрдЯ рдлрд▓ рджрд┐рдпрд╛ рдЗрд╕ рд╡реНрд░рддрдЪрд░реНрдпрд╛ рдХреА рд╕рдорд╛рдкреНрддрд┐ рдХреБрдорд╛рд░рд┐рдХрд╛рдУрдВ рдиреЗ рд╢реБрдХреНрд▓рдкрдХреНрд╖ рдорд╛рд░реНрдЧрд╢реАрд░реНрд╖ рдкреВрд░реНрдгрд┐рдорд╛ рдХреЗ рджрд┐рди рдХреА рдереАред

*Ordering a Pizza in 2022*

CALLER:
    Is this Pizza Hut?
 
GOOGLE:    
No sir, it's Google Pizza.
 
CALLER:  
I must have dialed a wrong number, sorry.
 
GOOGLE:  
No sir, Google bought Pizza Hut last month.
 
CALLER:  
OK. I would like to order a pizza.
 
GOOGLE:  
Do you want your usual, sir?
 
CALLER:
My usual? You know me?
 
GOOGLE:
According to our caller ID data sheet, the last 12 times you called you ordered an extra-large pizza with three cheeses, sausage, pepperoni, mushrooms and meatballs on a thick crust.
 
CALLER:  
Super! ThatтАЩs what IтАЩll have.
 
GOOGLE:
May I suggest that this time you order a pizza with ricotta, arugula, sun-dried tomatoes and olives on a whole wheat gluten-free thin crust?
 
CALLER:  
What? I donтАЩt want a vegetarian pizza!
 
GOOGLE:  
Your cholesterol is not good, sir.
 
CALLER:  
How the hell do you know that?
 
GOOGLE:
Well, we cross-referenced your home phone number with your medical records. We have the result of your blood tests for the last 7 years.
 
CALLER:
Okay, but I do not want your rotten vegetarian pizza!  I already take medication for my cholesterol.
 
GOOGLE:
Excuse me sir, but you have not taken your medication regularly.  According to our database, you purchased only a box of 30 cholesterol tablets once at Lloyds Pharmacy, 4 months ago.
 
CALLER:  
I bought more from another Pharmacy.
 
GOOGLE:  
That doesnтАЩt show on your credit card statement.
 
CALLER: 
I paid in cash.
 
GOOGLE:  
But you did not withdraw enough cash according to your bank statement.
 
CALLER:  
I have other sources of cash.
 
GOOGLE:
That doesnтАЩt show on your latest tax returns, unless you bought them using an undeclared income source, which is against the law!
 
CALLER:    
WHAT THE HELL!
 
GOOGLE:  
I'm sorry sir, we use such information only with the sole intention of helping you.
 
CALLER:  
Enough already!  I'm sick to death of Google, Facebook, Twitter, WhatsApp and all the others.  I'm going to an island without the internet, TV, where there is no phone service and no one to watch me or spy on me.
 
GOOGLE:      
I understand sir, but you need to renew your passport first. It expired 6 weeks ago...

2/9/21, 1:34 PM - Mom: The Chairman of TATA Steel was holding a weekly meeting with Tata Steel staff  in Jamshedpur. 
A worker took up a serious issue. 
He said the quality and hygiene of toilets for the workers was very bad.
Whereas, he  pointed that the cleaniness and the hygiene of executive toilets was always very good. 
The Chairman asked his top executive how much time he needs to set it right.
The executive asked for a month to set it right. 
Chairman said "I would rather do it in a day. Send me a carpenter." 
Next day, when the carpenter came, *he just ordered the sign boards to be swapped*. 
The sign board on the workersтАЩ toilet displayed "Executives" and the ExecutivesтАЩ toilet displayed "WorkersтАЭ.
Chairman then instructed this sign to be changed every fortnight.
The quality of both the toilets came at par in the next three days.  *Leadership is something much more than being an Executive** 

Moral :
Problem identification requires critical thinking.

**But solving a Problem just requires creative thinking_*
This is not a story. 
Regards ЁЯЩП

*E = 5 ; F = 6 ; G = 7 ; H = 8 ;*
*I = 9 ; J = 10 ; K = 11 ; L = 12 ;*
*M = 13 ; N = 14 ; O = 15 ; P = 16 ;*
*Q = 17 ; R = 18 ; S = 19 ; T = 20 ;*
*U = 21 ; V = 22 ; W = 23 ; X =24 ;*
*Y = 25 ; Z = 26.*

*Then,*

*H+A+R+D+W+O+R+K* 
=8+1+18+4+23+15+18+11
*= 98%*

*K+N+O+W+L+E+D+G+E*
=11+14+15+23+12+5+4+7+5
*=96%*

*L+O+V+E*
= 12+15+22+5 
*= 54%*

*L+U+C+K ;*
=12+21+3+11 
*= 47%*

*None of them makes 100%.*
*Then what makes 100%?*

*Is it Money?*
.
.
.
*NO!*

*M+O+N+E+Y*
= 13+15+14+5+25
*=72%*

*Leadership?*
.
.
.
*NO!*

*L+E+A+D+E+R+S+H+I+P*
=12+5+1+4+5+18+19+8+9+16
*=97%*

*Every problem has a solution, only if we perhaps change our*

     *"ATTITUDE"...*

*A+T+T+I+T+U+D+E ;*
1+20+20+9+20+21+4+5 
*= 100%*

*It is therefore OUR ATTITUDE towards Life* *and Work that makes*
*OUR Life 100% Successful.*

*Amazing mathematics*
 
*With each alphabet getting a number, in chronological order, as above, study the* *following, and bring down the total to a single digit and see the result yourself*

*Hindu -*
*S  h  r  e  e   K  r  i  s  h  n  a*
19+8+18+5+5+11+18+9+19+8+14+1
=135
*=1+3+5 = 9*

*Muslim*
*M  o  h  a  m  m  e  d*
13+15+8+1+13+13+5+4
= 72
*= 7+2 = 9*

*Jain*
*M a  h a v  i  r*
13+1+8+1+22+9+18
  =72
*= 7+2= 9*

*Sikh*
*G  u  r  u   N  a  n  a  k*
7+21+18+21+14+1+14+1+11 
=108 
*=1+0+8 = 9*

*Parsi*
*Z  a  r  a  t  h  u  s  t  r a*
26+1+18+1+20+8+21+19+20+18+1
=153
*=1+5+3 = 9*

*Buddhist*
*G  a   u  t  a  m*
7+1+21+20+1+13
=63
*= 6+3 = 9*

*Christian*
*E  s   a  M  e  s  s  i   a  h*
5+19+1+13+5+19+19+9+1+8
=99
9+9=18
*1+8 = 9*

*Each one ends with number  9*

5/2/21, 7:59 PM - Mom: Looks like the Indian COVID variant is here in Folsom.
One person, who is under 30, came back from India in mid-April, and got the Indian variant of the COVID. He is now in ICU. And few others are infected. 
It is impacting kids, and most people in 30s/40s. Even those who have taken both vaccine shots. 
So, there is a potential for spike in corona cases... especially in Indian community.
Please continue to wear masks and practice social distancing and avoid large indoor gatherings.
A San Ramon resident passed away on Apr 25 due to COVID-19 complications in India. He went to India to see his father. He got vaccinated before leaving (both shots). He got infected in India but tests were negative (apparently the latest strain only shows up on the CT scan) so he was caught unaware. Suddenly his oxygen level dropped to 70  and he had to be taken to the hospital. He was in a critical condition and then he passed away due to liver failure. He was a very healthy person. So looks like the vaccination might not be that effective for this new variant. 
Please be careful visiting India even after getting vaccinated. Take care and stay safe.
Dear Gujarati Samaj Members and community members at large.  Please note that this person is from Ahmedabad, Gujarat.  He is in critical condition and needs our collective prayers.  I strongly urge all (children, youth, young and not so young) to practice social distancing, wear masks, avoid gatherings (social and public) to protect us.  It is clear that the vaccine is NOT effective against this variant... BE EXTREMELY CAUTIOUS ... It appears that this person maintained isolation, and has had limited exposure both at work in Folsom and in friends circle... however, out of abundance of caution... avoid friends in Gujarati and Indian community for the next few months.

5/8/21, 6:20 AM - +1 (848) 219-4510: ЁЯЩПЁЯП╗ЁЯЩПЁЯП╗ЁЯЩПЁЯП╗
5/8/21, 7:00 PM - Sahil Sheth: *WHY RIP IS NOT THE CORRECT FORM OF CONDOLENCE TO A HINDU FAMILY*

R.I.P means Rest in Peace- In Christianity, this short epitaph signifies wishing rest and peace to someone who has died. Christians bury the dead ones and the soul rests in peace in that grave until the judgment day arrives. On the Judgment day, the Lord will decide who goes where- Heaven or Hell. They believe that on the Judgment day the dead will rise again. Until that time, the soul has to remain inside that coffin. Hence the blessing Rest In Peace (until the judgement day)

Now, Hinduism does not have any concept such as that of rising of dead ones. Hinduism believes in reincarnation. It says that the cycle of birth and death are governed by the Karma of individuals. The deceased individual would take another birth based upon the Karma of this life. So there is no rest and hence, the concept of RIP is not valid in Hinduism. Hinduism believes in Moksha that is liberation- Liberation from the endless cycles of birth and death. ThatтАЩs why instead of using RIP we should say, тАЬOm ShantiтАЭ or тАЬAatma Ko Sadgati Prapt Ho (May Soul attain Moksha)тАЭ or simply "Om Sadgati". Sadgati means salvation or liberation. We always pray that may the soul get liberated from the cycle of life and death.

In fact, the concept of RIP would remotely come close to the concept of Preta (Evil, hungry ghosts) which is basically a curse in the Hindu way of life. An individual after leaving his/her body becomes Preta. When we say RIP , we are praying for the soul to remain locked into a standstill on Earth as it becomes Preta for eternity. ThatтАЩs why in Hindu way of life there is a concept of Terahvin (13 days). For 13 days family members of deceased persuade the Pretas every day with various invocations and offerings requesting them to leave this earth and move on to their next destination which could be either incarnation or salvation (moksha). By saying _Om Sadgati_ we prompt the soul to move on and not remain in 'peace' here..

Share with your next generation children also as to why Hinduism don't say RIP when we send condolence messages.....

ркмрк╛ркХрлА *рккрккрлНрккрк╛ ркдрлЛ ркПрк╡рк╛ рккрк░ркорлЗрк╢рлНрк╡рк░* ркЫрлЗ ркЬрлЗркирлЗ рккрк╛ркорк╡рк╛ рк╡рлНрк░ркд, ркЙрккрк╡рк╛рк╕ ркХрлЗ ркЕркШрк░рк╛ рк╢рлНрк▓рлЛркХркирк╛ ркЧрк╛рки ркХрк░рк╡рк╛ ркиркерлА рккркбркдрк╛... ркЖрккркгрлА ркдркХрк▓рлАрклркорк╛ркВ ркЖрккркгрк╛ ркЦркнрк╛ркирлЗ ркЯрлЗркХрлЛ ркжрлЗрк╡рк╛ ркП ркЬрлАрк╡ркдрлЛ ркжрлЗрк╡ рк╣рк╛ркЬрк░рк╛ рк╣ркЬрлВрк░ ркЬ рк╣рлЛркп ркЫрлЗ.

рдЬреИрд╕реЗ :
1я╕ПтГг *рдЬрд▓реЗрдмреА*
рдЖрдХрд╛рд░ рдорд╛рдпрдиреЗ рдирд╣реАрдВ рд░рдЦрддрд╛, 
рд╕реНрд╡рднрд╛рд╡ рдорд╛рдпрдиреЗ рд░рдЦрддрд╛  рд╣реИ, 
рдЬреАрд╡рди рдореЗ рдЙрд▓рдЭрдиреЗ рдХрд┐рддрдиреА рднреА рд╣реЛ, *рд░рд╕реАрд▓реЗ рдФрд░ рдордзреБрд░ рд░рд╣реЛ* ре░ре░

2я╕ПтГг *рд░рд╕рдЧреБрд▓реНрд▓рд╛*
рдХреЛрдИ рдлрд░реНрдХ рдирд╣реАрдВ рдкрдбрд╝рддрд╛ рдХрд┐,
рдЬреАрд╡рди рдЖрдкрдХреЛ рдХрд┐рддрдирд╛ рдирд┐рдЪреЛрдбрд╝рддрд╛ рд╣реИ,
*рдЕрдкрдирд╛ рдЕрд╕рд▓реА рд░реВрдк рд╕рджрд╛ рдмрдирд╛рдпреЗ рд░рдЦреЗрдВ*

3я╕ПтГг *рд▓рдбреНрдбреВ*
рдмреВрдВрджреА-рдмреВрдВрджреА рд╕реЗ рд▓рдбреНрдбреВ рдмрдирддрд╛, рдЫреЛрдЯреЗ-рдЫреЛрдЯреЗ рдкреНрд░рдпрд╛рд╕ рд╕реЗ рд╣реА рд╕рдмрдХреБрдЫ рд╣реЛрддрд╛ рд╣реИрдВ!
*рд╕рдХрд╛рд░рд╛рддреНрдордХ рдкреНрд░рдпрд╛рд╕ рдХрд░рддреЗ рд░рд╣реЗ.* ре░ре░

4я╕ПтГг *рд╕реЛрд╣рди рдкрд╛рдкрдбрд╝реА*
рд╣рд░ рдХреЛрдИ рдЖрдкрдХреЛ рдкрд╕рдВрдж рдирд╣реАрдВ рдХрд░ рд╕рдХрддрд╛, рд▓реЗрдХрд┐рди рдмрдирд╛рдиреЗ рд╡рд╛рд▓реЗ рдиреЗ рдХрднреА рд╣рд┐рдореНрдордд рдирд╣реАрдВ рд╣рд╛рд░реАред
*рдЕрдкрдиреЗ рд▓рдХреНрд╖реНрдп рдкрд░ рдЯрд┐рдХреЗ рд░рд╣реЛ* ре░ре░

5я╕ПтГг *рдХрд╛рдЬреВ рдХрддрд▓реА*
рдЕрдкрдиреЗ рдЖрдк рдХреЛ рдЗрддрдирд╛ рд╕рд╕реНрддрд╛ рдирд╛ рд░рдЦреЗ,
рдХреА рд░рд╛рд╣ рдЪрд▓рддрд╛ рдХреЛрдИ рднреА рдЖрдкрдХрд╛ рджрд╛рдо рдкреВрдЫрддрд╛ рд░рд╣реЗ !
*рдЖрдВрддрд░рд┐рдХ рдЧреБрдгрд╡рддреНрддрд╛ рд╣рдореЗрдВ рд╕рдмрд╕реЗ рдЕрд▓рдЧ рдмрдирд╛рддреА рд╣реИ*

6я╕ПтГг *рдЧреБрд▓рд╛рдм рдЬрд╛рдореБрди*
рд╕реЙрдлреНрдЯ рд╣реЛрдирд╛ рдХрдордЬреЛрд░реА рдирд╣реАрдВ рд╣реИ! рдпреЗ рдЖрдкрдХреА рдЦрд╛рд╕рд┐рдпрдд рднреА рд╣реИред
*рдирдореНрд░рддрд╛ рдпрд╣ рдПрдХ рд╡рд┐рд╢реЗрд╖ рдЧреБрдг рд╣реИ*

7я╕ПтГг *рдмреЗрд╕рди рдХреЗ рд▓рдбреНрдбреВ*

ркИ.рк╕. рлзрлжрлпрлмркорк╛ркВ рк╕рк┐ркзрлНркзрк░рк╛ркЬ ркЬркпрк╕рк┐ркВрк╣ркирлЛ рк░рк╛ркЬрлНркпрк╛ркнрк┐рк╖рлЗркХ ркеркпрлЛ ркЕркирлЗ рлкрло рк╡рк░рлНрк╖ рк╕рлБркзрлА ркЕркЦркВркб рк╢рк╛рк╕рки ркХрк░рлНркпрлБркВ. ркЖ ркжрк░ркорк┐ркпрк╛рки ркЕркирлЗркХ ркпрлБркзрлНркз ркеркпрк╛ркВ рккрк░ркВркдрлБ рк╕рк┐ркзрлНркзрк░рк╛ркЬ ркЬркпрк╕рк┐ркВрк╣ рк╕ркжрк╛ рк╕рк░рлНрк╡ркжрк╛ ркЕрккрк░рк╛ркЬрк┐ркд рк░рк╛ркЬрк╛ рк░рк╣рлНркпрк╛.
ркИ.рк╕. рлзрлзрлйрллркорк╛ркВ рк░рк╛ркЬркорк╛ркдрк╛ ркорк┐ркирк│ркжрлЗрк╡рлА ркнркЧрк╡рк╛рки рк╢рлНрк░рлА ркХрлГрк╖рлНркгркирлА ркиркЧрк░рлА ркжрлЗрк╡ркнрлВркорк┐ ркжрлНрк╡рк╛рк░рк┐ркХрк╛ркирлА ркдрлАрк░рлНрке ркпрк╛ркдрлНрк░рк╛ркП ркЧркпрк╛ ркЕркирлЗ рккрк╛ркЫрк╛ рк╡рк│ркдрк╛ркВ рк╕ркоркпрлЗ рк╕рк┐ркзрлНркзрк░рк╛ркЬ ркЬркпрк╕рк┐ркВрк╣ рккрлЛркдрк╛ркирлА ркорк╛ркдрк╛ркирлЗ рк╕рк╛ркорлЗркерлА ркдрлЗркбрк╡рк╛ ркЧркпрк╛.
ркзркВркзрлБркХрк╛ ркиркЧрк░ркорк╛ркВ ркорк╛-ркжрлАркХрк░рк╛ркирлЛ рк╕рлБркЦркж ркорлЗрк│рк╛ркк ркеркпрлЛ рккрк░ркВркдрлБ ркдрлНркпрк╛ркВ ркЬ ркЧрлБрккрлНркдркЪрк░рлЛ ркжрлНрк╡рк╛рк░рк╛ рк╕ркорк╛ркЪрк╛рк░ ркорк│рлНркпрк╛ рк╣ркдрк╛ ркХрлЗ рк░рк╛ркЬрк╛ркирлА ркЧрлЗрк░рк╣рк╛ркЬрк░рлА рк╣рлЛрк╡рк╛ркерлА рк░рк╛ркЬркзрк╛ркирлА "ркЕркгрк╣рк┐рк▓рк╡рк╛ркб" (рккрлНрк░рк╡рк░рлНркдркорк╛рки рккрк╛ркЯркг ркиркЧрк░) ркЙрккрк░ ркорк╛рк│рк╡рк╛ркирк╛ рк░рк╛ркЬрк╛ ркпрк╢рк╡рк░рлНркорки/ркЕркиркВркдрк╡рк░рлНркоркиркП рк╕ркорк╕рлНркд рк╕рлИркирлНркп рк╕рк╣рк┐ркд рккрлВрк░рлНркг рк╢ркХрлНркдрк┐ркерлА ркЖркХрлНрк░ркоркг ркХрк░рлНркпрлБркВ рк╣ркдрлБркВ.
ркПркХрккркг ркпрлБркжрлНркз рки рк╣рк╛рк░рлЗрк▓рк╛ рк░рк╛ркЬрк╛ рк╕рк┐ркзрлНркзрк░рк╛ркЬ ркЬркпрк╕рк┐ркВрк╣ рклрк░рлА ркПркХрк╡рк╛рк░ ркорк╛рк│рк╡рк╛ркирк╛ рк░рк╛ркЬрк╛ ркпрк╢рк╡рк░рлНркорки/ркЕркиркВркдрк╡рк░рлНркоркиркирлЗ рккрк░рк╛ркЬрк┐ркд ркХрк░рлЗ ркЫрлЗ. (ркИ.рк╕. рлзрлзрлйрлл)
рк╣рк╛рк░рлЗрк▓рлЛ рк░рк╛ркЬрк╛ ркЬрлАркдрлЗрк▓рк╛ рк░рк╛ркЬрк╛ркирлА ркЖркзрк┐ркиркдрк╛ рк╕рлНрк╡рлАркХрк╛рк░рлЗ ркЫрлЗ ркЕркирлЗ рккрлНрк░ркдрлНркпрлЗркХ рк╡рк░рлНрк╖ ркЦркВркбркгрлА ркнрк░рк╡рк╛ркирлБркВ ркиркХрлНркХрлА ркХрк░рлЗ ркЫрлЗ, рккрк░ркВркдрлБ рк╣рк╛рк░рлЗрк▓рлЛ рк░рк╛ркЬрк╛ ркпрк╢рк╡рк░рлНркорки/ркЕркиркВркдрк╡рк░рлНркорки ркЬрлАркдрлЗрк▓рк╛ рк░рк╛ркЬрк╛ рк╕рк┐ркжрлНркзрк░рк╛ркЬ ркЬркпрк╕рк┐ркВрк╣ркирлЗ ркорк╣рлЗркгрлБркВ ркорк╛рк░рлЗ ркЫрлЗ, "рк╣рлЗ рк░рк╛ркЬрки! ркдрк╛рк░рк╛ рк╕ркорлГркжрлНркз ркЧрлБрк░рлНркЬрк░ рккрлНрк░ркжрлЗрк╢ркорк╛ркВ ркдркорк╛рк░рк╛ рк░рк╛ркЬрлНркпркирлА ркХрлЛркИ рк░рк╛ркЬ ркнрк╛рк╖рк╛ ркиркерлА?"
ркЖркЯрк▓рлБркВ рк╕рк╛ркВркнрк│ркдрк╛ ркЬ ркЬрк▓рк╡ркВркд ркЬрлАркдркирлЛ ркирк╢рлЛ ркЪркХркирк╛ркЪрлВрк░ ркеркИ ркЧркпрлЛ. рк╕рк┐ркзрлНркзрк░рк╛ркЬ ркЬркпрк╕рк┐ркВрк╣ ркЖркЦрлА рк░рк╛ркд рк╕рлБркИ рки рк╢ркХрлНркпрлЛ.

ркЧрлБркЬрк░рк╛ркдрлА ркнрк╛рк╖рк╛ркирлА рк░ркЪркирк╛ :-

рккрлНрк░ркнрк╛ркд ркеркдрк╛ркВ ркЬ рк╕рк┐ркзрлНркзрк░рк╛ркЬ ркЬркпрк╕рк┐ркВрк╣ркирлЛ ркирк╡рлА ркнрк╛рк╖рк╛ ркмркирк╛рк╡рлЗ ркдрлЗрк╡рк╛ рк╡рк┐ркжрлНрк╡рк╛рки ркорк╣рк╛рккрлБрк░рлБрк╖ ркЬрлИркирк╛ркЪрк╛рк░рлНркп ркХрк▓рк┐ркХрк╛рк▓ркЬрлНркЮ рк╕рк░рлНрк╡ркЬрлНркЮ рк╣рлЗркоркЪркВркжрлНрк░рк╛ркЪрк╛рк░рлНркпркирлЛ ркнрлЗркЯрлЛ ркеркпрлЛ.
рк╕ркВрк╕рлНркХрлГркд, рккрлНрк░рк╛ркХрлГркд, ркЕркирлЗ рккрк╛рк▓рлА ркПрко рлй ркнрк╛рк╖рк╛ркирк╛ рк╡рлНркпрк╛ркХрк░ркгркирлЛ рк╢рлБркХрлНрк╖рлНркоркдрк╛рккрлБрк░рлНрк╡ркХ ркКркВркбрлЛ ркЕркнрлНркпрк╛рк╕ ркХрк░рлАркирлЗ рк╣рлЗркоркЪркВркжрлНрк░рк╛ркЪрк╛рк░рлНркп ркП ркИ.рк╕. рлзрлзрлйрллркорк╛ркВ ркЧрлБркЬрк░рк╛ркдрлА ркнрк╛рк╖рк╛ркирлА рк░ркЪркирк╛ ркХрк░рлА.

рк╕ркорк╛рккрки :-

ркдрлЗ рк╕ркоркпрлЗ рк╣рк╛ркерлАркирлА ркЕркВркмрк╛ркбрлА ркЙрккрк░ ркмрлЗрк╕рк╛ркбрлАркирлЗ рк╕рк░рлНрк╡рлЛркЪрлНркЪ рк╕ркирлНркорк╛рки ркЕрккрк╛ркдрлБркВ рк╣ркдрлБркВ.
рк╣рлЗркоркЪркВркжрлНрк░рк╛ркЪрк╛рк░рлНркп ркжрлНрк╡рк╛рк░рк╛ рк░ркЪрк┐ркд рк╡рлНркпрк╛ркХрк░ркг ркЧрлНрк░ркВрке "рк╕рк┐ркзрлНркз рк╣рлЗрко рк╢ркмрлНркжрк╛ркирлБрк╢рк╛рк╕рки" ркирлЗ рк╣рк╛ркерлАркирлА ркЕркВркмрк╛ркбрлА ркЙрккрк░ рк╕рлНркерк╛рккрк┐ркд ркХрк░рлАркирлЗ ркдрлЗ рк╕ркоркпрлЗ рлз,рлжрлж,рлжрлжрлж ркирлА рк╡рк╕рлНркдрлА ркзрк░рк╛рк╡ркдрк╛ "ркЕркгрк╣рк┐рк▓рк╡рк╛ркб рккрлБрк░" (рккрк╛ркЯркг)ркорк╛ркВ ркдрлЗркирлА рк╢рлЛркнрк╛ркпрк╛ркдрлНрк░рк╛ ркХрк╛ркврк╡рк╛ркорк╛ркВ ркЖрк╡рлА.
ркдрлЗ рк╕ркоркпрлЗ рк▓ркЧркнркЧ рлзрллрлжрлж ркЬрлИрки рк╕рк╛ркзрлБркУркП ркЖ ркнрк╛рк╖рк╛ рк╕ркоркЧрлНрк░ ркЧрлБркЬрк░рк╛ркд рк░рк╛ркЬрлНркпркорк╛ркВ рк╢рлАркЦрк╡рлА ркЕркирлЗ ркорк╛ркдрлНрк░ рллрлж рк╡рк░рлНрк╖ рккрк╢рлНрк╡рк╛ркд ркЧрлБркЬрк░рк╛ркдрлА ркнрк╛рк╖рк╛ркирлА рк╕рк░рлНрк╡ рккрлНрк░ркерко ркирк╡рк▓ркХркерк╛ ркнрк░ркдрлЗрк╢рлНрк╡рк░ ркмрк╛рк╣рлБркмрк▓рлА рк░рк╛рк╕ рккркг рк▓ркЦрк╛ркИ.
